80 Reduction JSNativeContextSpecialization::Reduce(Node* node) {
81  switch (node->opcode()) {
82  case IrOpcode::kJSAdd:
83  return ReduceJSAdd(node);
84  case IrOpcode::kJSAsyncFunctionEnter:
85  return ReduceJSAsyncFunctionEnter(node);
86  case IrOpcode::kJSAsyncFunctionReject:
87  return ReduceJSAsyncFunctionReject(node);
88  case IrOpcode::kJSAsyncFunctionResolve:
89  return ReduceJSAsyncFunctionResolve(node);
90  case IrOpcode::kJSGetSuperConstructor:
91  return ReduceJSGetSuperConstructor(node);
92  case IrOpcode::kJSFindNonDefaultConstructorOrConstruct:
93  return ReduceJSFindNonDefaultConstructorOrConstruct(node);
94  case IrOpcode::kJSInstanceOf:
95  return ReduceJSInstanceOf(node);
96  case IrOpcode::kJSHasInPrototypeChain:
97  return ReduceJSHasInPrototypeChain(node);
98  case IrOpcode::kJSOrdinaryHasInstance:
99  return ReduceJSOrdinaryHasInstance(node);
100  case IrOpcode::kJSPromiseResolve:
101  return ReduceJSPromiseResolve(node);
102  case IrOpcode::kJSResolvePromise:
103  return ReduceJSResolvePromise(node);
104  case IrOpcode::kJSLoadGlobal:
105  return ReduceJSLoadGlobal(node);
106  case IrOpcode::kJSStoreGlobal:
107  return ReduceJSStoreGlobal(node);
108  case IrOpcode::kJSLoadNamed:
109  return ReduceJSLoadNamed(node);
110  case IrOpcode::kJSLoadNamedFromSuper:
111  return ReduceJSLoadNamedFromSuper(node);
112  case IrOpcode::kJSSetNamedProperty:
113  return ReduceJSSetNamedProperty(node);
114  case IrOpcode::kJSHasProperty:
115  return ReduceJSHasProperty(node);
116  case IrOpcode::kJSLoadProperty:
117  return ReduceJSLoadProperty(node);
118  case IrOpcode::kJSSetKeyedProperty:
119  return ReduceJSSetKeyedProperty(node);
120  case IrOpcode::kJSDefineKeyedOwnProperty:
121  return ReduceJSDefineKeyedOwnProperty(node);
122  case IrOpcode::kJSDefineNamedOwnProperty:
123  return ReduceJSDefineNamedOwnProperty(node);
124  case IrOpcode::kJSDefineKeyedOwnPropertyInLiteral:
125  return ReduceJSDefineKeyedOwnPropertyInLiteral(node);
126  case IrOpcode::kJSStoreInArrayLiteral:
127  return ReduceJSStoreInArrayLiteral(node);
128  case IrOpcode::kJSToObject:
129  return ReduceJSToObject(node);
130  case IrOpcode::kJSToString:
131  return ReduceJSToString(node);
132  case IrOpcode::kJSGetIterator:
133  return ReduceJSGetIterator(node);
134  default:
135  break;
136  }
137  return NoChange();
138 }

140 // If {node} is a HeapConstant<String>, return the String's length. If {node} is
141 // a number, return the maximum size that a stringified number can have.
142 // Otherwise, we can't easily convert {node} into a String, and we return
143 // nullopt.
144 // static
145 std::optional<size_t> JSNativeContextSpecialization::GetMaxStringLength(
146  JSHeapBroker* broker, Node* node) {
147  HeapObjectMatcher matcher(node);
148  if (matcher.HasResolvedValue() && matcher.Ref(broker).IsString()) {
149  StringRef input = matcher.Ref(broker).AsString();
150  return input.length();
151  }
152 
153  NumberMatcher number_matcher(node);
154  if (number_matcher.HasResolvedValue()) {
155  return kMaxDoubleStringLength;
156  }
157 
158  // We don't support objects with possibly monkey-patched prototype.toString
159  // as it might have side-effects, so we shouldn't attempt lowering them.
160  return std::nullopt;
161 }

163 Reduction JSNativeContextSpecialization::ReduceJSToString(Node* node) {
164  DCHECK_EQ(IrOpcode::kJSToString, node->opcode());
165  Node* const input = node->InputAt(0);
166 
167  HeapObjectMatcher matcher(input);
168  if (matcher.HasResolvedValue() && matcher.Ref(broker()).IsString()) {
169  Reduction reduction = Changed(input); // JSToString(x:string) => x
170  ReplaceWithValue(node, reduction.replacement());
171  return reduction;
172  }
173 
174  // TODO(turbofan): This optimization is weaker than what we used to have
175  // in js-typed-lowering for OrderedNumbers. We don't have types here though,
176  // so alternative approach should be designed if this causes performance
177  // regressions and the stronger optimization should be re-implemented.
178  NumberMatcher number_matcher(input);
179  if (number_matcher.HasResolvedValue()) {
180  Handle<String> num_str =
181  broker()->local_isolate_or_isolate()->factory()->DoubleToString(
182  number_matcher.ResolvedValue());
183  Node* reduced = graph()->NewNode(
184  common()->HeapConstant(broker()->CanonicalPersistentHandle(num_str)));
185 
186  ReplaceWithValue(node, reduced);
187  return Replace(reduced);
188  }
189 
190  return NoChange();
191 }

193 // Return a String from {node}, which should be either a HeapConstant<String>
194 // (in which case we return the String), or a number (in which case we convert
195 // it to a String).
196 Handle<String> JSNativeContextSpecialization::CreateStringConstant(Node* node) {
197  DCHECK(IrOpcode::IsConstantOpcode(node->opcode()));
198  NumberMatcher number_matcher(node);
199  if (number_matcher.HasResolvedValue()) {
200  // Note that we do not store the result of NumberToString in
201  // {created_strings_}, because the latter is used to know if strings are
202  // safe to be used in the background, but we always have as additional
203  // information the node from which the string was created ({node} is that
204  // case), and if this node is a kHeapNumber, then we know that we must have
205  // created the string, and that there it is safe to read. So, we don't need
206  // {created_strings_} in that case.
207  return broker()->local_isolate_or_isolate()->factory()->DoubleToString(
208  number_matcher.ResolvedValue());
209  } else {
210  HeapObjectMatcher matcher(node);
211  if (matcher.HasResolvedValue() && matcher.Ref(broker()).IsString()) {
212  return matcher.Ref(broker()).AsString().object();
213  } else {
214  UNREACHABLE();
215  }
216  }
217 }

220 bool IsStringConstant(JSHeapBroker* broker, Node* node) {
221  HeapObjectMatcher matcher(node);
222  return matcher.HasResolvedValue() && matcher.Ref(broker).IsString();
223 }

225 bool IsStringWithNonAccessibleContent(JSHeapBroker* broker, Node* node) {
226  HeapObjectMatcher matcher(node);
227  if (matcher.HasResolvedValue() && matcher.Ref(broker).IsString()) {
228  StringRef input = matcher.Ref(broker).AsString();
229  return !input.IsContentAccessible();
230  }
231  return false;
232 }

235 Reduction JSNativeContextSpecialization::ReduceJSAsyncFunctionEnter(
236  Node* node) {
237  DCHECK_EQ(IrOpcode::kJSAsyncFunctionEnter, node->opcode());
238  Node* closure = NodeProperties::GetValueInput(node, 0);
239  Node* receiver = NodeProperties::GetValueInput(node, 1);
240  Node* context = NodeProperties::GetContextInput(node);
241  Node* frame_state = NodeProperties::GetFrameStateInput(node);
242  Node* effect = NodeProperties::GetEffectInput(node);
243  Node* control = NodeProperties::GetControlInput(node);
244 
245  if (!dependencies()->DependOnPromiseHookProtector()) return NoChange();
246 
247  // Create the promise for the async function.
248  Node* promise = effect =
249  graph()->NewNode(javascript()->CreatePromise(), context, effect);
250 
251  // Create the JSAsyncFunctionObject based on the BytecodeArray
252  // extracted from the top-most frame in {frame_state}.
253  FrameStateInfo state_info = FrameStateInfoOf(frame_state->op());
254  Handle<BytecodeArray> bytecode_array =
255  state_info.bytecode_array().ToHandleChecked();
256  DCHECK_EQ(state_info.shared_info()
257  .ToHandleChecked()
258  ->internal_formal_parameter_count_without_receiver(),
259  bytecode_array->parameter_count_without_receiver());
260  int register_count = bytecode_array->parameter_count_without_receiver() +
261  bytecode_array->register_count();
262  MapRef fixed_array_map = broker()->fixed_array_map();
263  AllocationBuilder ab(jsgraph(), broker(), effect, control);
264  if (!ab.CanAllocateArray(register_count, fixed_array_map)) {
265  return NoChange();
266  }
267  Node* value = effect =
268  graph()->NewNode(javascript()->CreateAsyncFunctionObject(register_count),
269  closure, receiver, promise, context, effect, control);
270  ReplaceWithValue(node, value, effect, control);
271  return Replace(value);
272 }

274 Reduction JSNativeContextSpecialization::ReduceJSAsyncFunctionReject(
275  Node* node) {
276  DCHECK_EQ(IrOpcode::kJSAsyncFunctionReject, node->opcode());
277  Node* async_function_object = NodeProperties::GetValueInput(node, 0);
278  Node* reason = NodeProperties::GetValueInput(node, 1);
279  Node* context = NodeProperties::GetContextInput(node);
280  Node* frame_state = NodeProperties::GetFrameStateInput(node);
281  Node* effect = NodeProperties::GetEffectInput(node);
282  Node* control = NodeProperties::GetControlInput(node);
283 
284  if (!dependencies()->DependOnPromiseHookProtector()) return NoChange();
285 
286  // Load the promise from the {async_function_object}.
287  Node* promise = effect = graph()->NewNode(
288  simplified()->LoadField(AccessBuilder::ForJSAsyncFunctionObjectPromise()),
289  async_function_object, effect, control);
290 
291  // Create a nested frame state inside the current method's most-recent
292  // {frame_state} that will ensure that lazy deoptimizations at this
293  // point will still return the {promise} instead of the result of the
294  // JSRejectPromise operation (which yields undefined).
295  Node* parameters[] = {promise};
296  frame_state = CreateStubBuiltinContinuationFrameState(
297  jsgraph(), Builtin::kAsyncFunctionLazyDeoptContinuation, context,
298  parameters, arraysize(parameters), frame_state,
299  ContinuationFrameStateMode::LAZY);
300 
301  // Disable the additional debug event for the rejection since a
302  // debug event already happend for the exception that got us here.
303  Node* debug_event = jsgraph()->FalseConstant();
304  effect = graph()->NewNode(javascript()->RejectPromise(), promise, reason,
305  debug_event, context, frame_state, effect, control);
306  ReplaceWithValue(node, promise, effect, control);
307  return Replace(promise);
308 }

310 Reduction JSNativeContextSpecialization::ReduceJSAsyncFunctionResolve(
311  Node* node) {
312  DCHECK_EQ(IrOpcode::kJSAsyncFunctionResolve, node->opcode());
313  Node* async_function_object = NodeProperties::GetValueInput(node, 0);
314  Node* value = NodeProperties::GetValueInput(node, 1);
315  Node* context = NodeProperties::GetContextInput(node);
316  Node* frame_state = NodeProperties::GetFrameStateInput(node);
317  Node* effect = NodeProperties::GetEffectInput(node);
318  Node* control = NodeProperties::GetControlInput(node);
319 
320  if (!dependencies()->DependOnPromiseHookProtector()) return NoChange();
321 
322  // Load the promise from the {async_function_object}.
323  Node* promise = effect = graph()->NewNode(
324  simplified()->LoadField(AccessBuilder::ForJSAsyncFunctionObjectPromise()),
325  async_function_object, effect, control);
326 
327  // Create a nested frame state inside the current method's most-recent
328  // {frame_state} that will ensure that lazy deoptimizations at this
329  // point will still return the {promise} instead of the result of the
330  // JSResolvePromise operation (which yields undefined).
331  Node* parameters[] = {promise};
332  frame_state = CreateStubBuiltinContinuationFrameState(
333  jsgraph(), Builtin::kAsyncFunctionLazyDeoptContinuation, context,
334  parameters, arraysize(parameters), frame_state,
335  ContinuationFrameStateMode::LAZY);
336 
337  effect = graph()->NewNode(javascript()->ResolvePromise(), promise, value,
338  context, frame_state, effect, control);
339  ReplaceWithValue(node, promise, effect, control);
340  return Replace(promise);
341 }

343 // Concatenates {left} and {right}. The result is fairly similar to creating a
344 // new ConsString with {left} and {right} and then flattening it, which we don't
345 // do because String::Flatten does not support background threads. Rather than
346 // implementing a full String::Flatten for background threads, we prefered to
347 // implement this Concatenate function, which, unlike String::Flatten, doesn't
348 // need to replace ConsStrings by ThinStrings.
349 Handle<String> JSNativeContextSpecialization::Concatenate(
350  Handle<String> left, Handle<String> right) {
351  if (left->length() == 0) return right;
352  if (right->length() == 0) return left;
353 
354  // Repeated concatenations have a quadratic cost (eg, "s+=a;s+=b;s+=c;...").
355  // Rather than doing static analysis to determine how many concatenations we
356  // there are and how many uses the result of each concatenation have, we
357  // generate ConsString when the result of the concatenation would have more
358  // than {kConstantStringFlattenMaxSize} characters, and flattened SeqString
359  // otherwise.
360  // TODO(dmercadier): ideally, we would like to get rid of this constant, and
361  // always flatten. This requires some care to avoid the quadratic worst-case.
362  constexpr int32_t kConstantStringFlattenMaxSize = 100;
363 
364  int32_t length = left->length() + right->length();
365  if (length > kConstantStringFlattenMaxSize) {
366  // The generational write-barrier doesn't work in background threads, so,
367  // if {left} or {right} are in the young generation, we would have to copy
368  // them to the local heap (which is old) before creating the (old)
369  // ConsString. But, copying a ConsString instead of flattening it to a
370  // SeqString makes no sense here (since flattening would be faster and use
371  // less memory). Thus, if one of {left} or {right} is a young string, we'll
372  // build a SeqString rather than a ConsString, regardless of {length}.
373  // TODO(dmercadier, dinfuehr): always build a ConsString here once the
374  // generational write-barrier supports background threads.
375  if (!LocalHeap::Current() || (!HeapLayout::InYoungGeneration(*left) &&
376  !HeapLayout::InYoungGeneration(*right))) {
377  return broker()
378  ->local_isolate_or_isolate()
379  ->factory()
380  ->NewConsString(left, right, AllocationType::kOld)
381  .ToHandleChecked();
382  }
383  }
384 
385  // If one of the string is not in readonly space, then we need a
386  // SharedStringAccessGuardIfNeeded before accessing its content.
387  bool require_guard = SharedStringAccessGuardIfNeeded::IsNeeded(
388  *left, broker()->local_isolate_or_isolate()) ||
389  SharedStringAccessGuardIfNeeded::IsNeeded(
390  *right, broker()->local_isolate_or_isolate());
391 
392  // Check string representation of both strings. This does not require the
393  // SharedStringAccessGuardIfNeeded as the representation is stable.
394  const bool result_is_one_byte_string =
395  left->IsOneByteRepresentation() && right->IsOneByteRepresentation();
396 
397  if (result_is_one_byte_string) {
398  // {left} and {right} are 1-byte ==> the result will be 1-byte.
399  // Note that we need a canonical handle, because we insert in
400  // {created_strings_} the handle's address, which is kinda meaningless if
401  // the handle isn't canonical.
402  Handle<SeqOneByteString> flat = broker()->CanonicalPersistentHandle(
403  broker()
404  ->local_isolate_or_isolate()
405  ->factory()
406  ->NewRawOneByteString(length, AllocationType::kOld)
407  .ToHandleChecked());
408  created_strings_.insert(flat);
409  DisallowGarbageCollection no_gc;
410  SharedStringAccessGuardIfNeeded access_guard(
411  require_guard ? broker()->local_isolate_or_isolate() : nullptr);
412  String::WriteToFlat(*left, flat->GetChars(no_gc, access_guard), 0,
413  left->length(), access_guard);
414  String::WriteToFlat(*right,
415  flat->GetChars(no_gc, access_guard) + left->length(), 0,
416  right->length(), access_guard);
417  return flat;
418  } else {
419  // One (or both) of {left} and {right} is 2-byte ==> the result will be
420  // 2-byte.
421  Handle<SeqTwoByteString> flat = broker()->CanonicalPersistentHandle(
422  broker()
423  ->local_isolate_or_isolate()
424  ->factory()
425  ->NewRawTwoByteString(length, AllocationType::kOld)
426  .ToHandleChecked());
427  created_strings_.insert(flat);
428  DisallowGarbageCollection no_gc;
429  SharedStringAccessGuardIfNeeded access_guard(
430  require_guard ? broker()->local_isolate_or_isolate() : nullptr);
431  String::WriteToFlat(*left, flat->GetChars(no_gc, access_guard), 0,
432  left->length(), access_guard);
433  String::WriteToFlat(*right,
434  flat->GetChars(no_gc, access_guard) + left->length(), 0,
435  right->length(), access_guard);
436  return flat;
437  }
438 }

440 bool JSNativeContextSpecialization::StringCanSafelyBeRead(Node* const node,
441  Handle<String> str) {
442  DCHECK(node->opcode() == IrOpcode::kHeapConstant ||
443  node->opcode() == IrOpcode::kNumberConstant);
444  if (broker()->IsMainThread()) {
445  // All strings are safe to be read on the main thread.
446  return true;
447  }
448  if (node->opcode() == IrOpcode::kNumberConstant) {
449  // If {node} is a number constant, then {str} is the stringification of this
450  // number which we must have created ourselves.
451  return true;
452  }
453  return !IsStringWithNonAccessibleContent(broker(), node) ||
454  created_strings_.find(str) != created_strings_.end();
455 }

457 Reduction JSNativeContextSpecialization::ReduceJSAdd(Node* node) {
458  // TODO(turbofan): This has to run together with the inlining and
459  // native context specialization to be able to leverage the string
460  // constant-folding for optimizing property access, but we should
461  // nevertheless find a better home for this at some point.
462  DCHECK_EQ(IrOpcode::kJSAdd, node->opcode());
463 
464  Node* const lhs = node->InputAt(0);
465  Node* const rhs = node->InputAt(1);
466 
467  std::optional<size_t> lhs_len = GetMaxStringLength(broker(), lhs);
468  std::optional<size_t> rhs_len = GetMaxStringLength(broker(), rhs);
469  if (!lhs_len || !rhs_len) return NoChange();
470 
471  // Fold if at least one of the parameters is a string constant and the
472  // addition won't throw due to too long result.
473  if (*lhs_len + *rhs_len <= String::kMaxLength &&
474  (IsStringConstant(broker(), lhs) || IsStringConstant(broker(), rhs))) {
475  // We need canonical handles for {left} and {right}, in order to be able to
476  // search {created_strings_} if needed.
477  Handle<String> left =
478  broker()->CanonicalPersistentHandle(CreateStringConstant(lhs));
479  Handle<String> right =
480  broker()->CanonicalPersistentHandle(CreateStringConstant(rhs));
481 
482  if (!(StringCanSafelyBeRead(lhs, left) &&
483  StringCanSafelyBeRead(rhs, right))) {
484  // One of {lhs} or {rhs} is not safe to be read in the background.
485 
486  if (left->length() + right->length() > ConsString::kMinLength &&
487  (!LocalHeap::Current() || (!HeapLayout::InYoungGeneration(*left) &&
488  !HeapLayout::InYoungGeneration(*right)))) {
489  // We can create a ConsString with {left} and {right}, without needing
490  // to read their content (and this ConsString will not introduce
491  // old-to-new pointers from the background).
492  Handle<String> concatenated =
493  broker()
494  ->local_isolate_or_isolate()
495  ->factory()
496  ->NewConsString(left, right, AllocationType::kOld)
497  .ToHandleChecked();
498  Node* reduced = graph()->NewNode(common()->HeapConstant(
499  broker()->CanonicalPersistentHandle(concatenated)));
500  ReplaceWithValue(node, reduced);
501  return Replace(reduced);
502  } else {
503  // Concatenating those strings would not produce a ConsString but rather
504  // a flat string (because the result is small). And, since the strings
505  // are not safe to be read in the background, this wouldn't be safe.
506  // Or, one of the string is in the young generation, and since the
507  // generational barrier doesn't support background threads, we cannot
508  // create the ConsString.
509  return NoChange();
510  }
511  }
512 
513  Handle<String> concatenated = Concatenate(left, right);
514  Node* reduced = graph()->NewNode(common()->HeapConstant(
515  broker()->CanonicalPersistentHandle(concatenated)));
516 
517  ReplaceWithValue(node, reduced);
518  return Replace(reduced);
519  }
520 
521  return NoChange();
522 }

524 Reduction JSNativeContextSpecialization::ReduceJSGetSuperConstructor(
525  Node* node) {
526  DCHECK_EQ(IrOpcode::kJSGetSuperConstructor, node->opcode());
527  Node* constructor = NodeProperties::GetValueInput(node, 0);
528 
529  // Check if the input is a known JSFunction.
530  HeapObjectMatcher m(constructor);
531  if (!m.HasResolvedValue() || !m.Ref(broker()).IsJSFunction()) {
532  return NoChange();
533  }
534  JSFunctionRef function = m.Ref(broker()).AsJSFunction();
535  MapRef function_map = function.map(broker());
536  HeapObjectRef function_prototype = function_map.prototype(broker());
537 
538  // We can constant-fold the super constructor access if the
539  // {function}s map is stable, i.e. we can use a code dependency
540  // to guard against [[Prototype]] changes of {function}.
541  if (function_map.is_stable()) {
542  dependencies()->DependOnStableMap(function_map);
543  Node* value = jsgraph()->ConstantNoHole(function_prototype, broker());
544  ReplaceWithValue(node, value);
545  return Replace(value);
546  }
547 
548  return NoChange();
549 }

551 Reduction
552 JSNativeContextSpecialization::ReduceJSFindNonDefaultConstructorOrConstruct(
553  Node* node) {
554  JSFindNonDefaultConstructorOrConstructNode n(node);
555  Node* this_function = n.this_function();
556  Node* new_target = n.new_target();
557  Node* effect = n.effect();
558  Control control = n.control();
559 
560  // If the JSFindNonDefaultConstructorOrConstruct operation is inside a try
561  // catch, wiring up the graph is complex (reason: if
562  // JSFindNonDefaultConstructorOrConstruct reduces to a constant which is
563  // something else than a default base ctor, it cannot throw an exception, and
564  // the try-catch structure has to be rewired). As this use case is rare, give
565  // up optimizing it here.
566  if (NodeProperties::IsExceptionalCall(node)) {
567  return NoChange();
568  }
569 
570  // TODO(v8:13091): Don't produce incomplete stack traces when debug is active.
571  // We already deopt when a breakpoint is set. But it would be even nicer to
572  // avoid producting incomplete stack traces when when debug is active, even if
573  // there are no breakpoints - then a user inspecting stack traces via Dev
574  // Tools would always see the full stack trace.
575 
576  // Check if the input is a known JSFunction.
577  HeapObjectMatcher m(this_function);
578  if (!m.HasResolvedValue() || !m.Ref(broker()).IsJSFunction()) {
579  return NoChange();
580  }
581 
582  JSFunctionRef this_function_ref = m.Ref(broker()).AsJSFunction();
583  MapRef function_map = this_function_ref.map(broker());
584  HeapObjectRef current = function_map.prototype(broker());
585  // The uppermost JSFunction on the class hierarchy (above it, there can be
586  // other JSObjects, e.g., Proxies).
587  OptionalJSObjectRef last_function;
588 
589  Node* return_value;
590  Node* ctor_or_instance;
591 
592  // Walk the class inheritance tree until we find a ctor which is not a default
593  // derived ctor.
594  while (true) {
595  if (!current.IsJSFunction()) {
596  return NoChange();
597  }
598  JSFunctionRef current_function = current.AsJSFunction();
599 
600  // If there are class fields, bail out. TODO(v8:13091): Handle them here.
601  if (current_function.shared(broker())
602  .requires_instance_members_initializer()) {
603  return NoChange();
604  }
605 
606  // If there are private methods, bail out. TODO(v8:13091): Handle them here.
607  if (current_function.context(broker())
608  .scope_info(broker())
609  .ClassScopeHasPrivateBrand()) {
610  return NoChange();
611  }
612 
613  FunctionKind kind = current_function.shared(broker()).kind();
614 
615  if (kind != FunctionKind::kDefaultDerivedConstructor) {
616  // The hierarchy walk will end here; this is the last change to bail out
617  // before creating new nodes.
618  if (!dependencies()->DependOnArrayIteratorProtector()) {
619  return NoChange();
620  }
621  last_function = current_function;
622 
623  if (kind == FunctionKind::kDefaultBaseConstructor) {
624  return_value = jsgraph()->BooleanConstant(true);
625 
626  // Generate a builtin call for creating the instance.
627  Node* constructor =
628  jsgraph()->ConstantNoHole(current_function, broker());
629 
630  // In the current FrameState setup, the two outputs of this bytecode are
631  // poked at indices slot(index(reg_2)) (boolean_output) and
632  // slot(index(reg_2) + 1) (object_output). Now we're reducing this
633  // bytecode to a builtin call which only has one output (object_output).
634  // Change where in the FrameState the output is poked at.
635 
636  // The current poke location points to the location for boolean_ouput.
637  // We move the poke location by -1, since the poke location decreases
638  // when the register index increases (see
639  // BytecodeGraphBuilder::Environment::BindRegistersToProjections).
640 
641  // The location for boolean_output is already hard-wired to true (which
642  // is the correct value here) in
643  // BytecodeGraphBuilder::VisitFindNonDefaultConstructorOrConstruct.
644 
645  FrameState old_frame_state = n.frame_state();
646  auto old_poke_offset = old_frame_state.frame_state_info()
647  .state_combine()
648  .GetOffsetToPokeAt();
649  FrameState new_frame_state = CloneFrameState(
650  jsgraph(), old_frame_state,
651  OutputFrameStateCombine::PokeAt(old_poke_offset - 1));
652 
653  effect = ctor_or_instance = graph()->NewNode(
654  jsgraph()->javascript()->Create(), constructor, new_target,
655  n.context(), new_frame_state, effect, control);
656  } else {
657  return_value = jsgraph()->BooleanConstant(false);
658  ctor_or_instance =
659  jsgraph()->ConstantNoHole(current_function, broker());
660  }
661  break;
662  }
663 
664  // Keep walking up the class tree.
665  current = current_function.map(broker()).prototype(broker());
666  }
667 
668  dependencies()->DependOnStablePrototypeChain(
669  function_map, WhereToStart::kStartAtReceiver, last_function);
670 
671  // Update the uses of {node}.
672  for (Edge edge : node->use_edges()) {
673  Node* const user = edge.from();
674  if (NodeProperties::IsEffectEdge(edge)) {
675  edge.UpdateTo(effect);
676  } else if (NodeProperties::IsControlEdge(edge)) {
677  edge.UpdateTo(control);
678  } else {
679  DCHECK(NodeProperties::IsValueEdge(edge));
680  switch (ProjectionIndexOf(user->op())) {
681  case 0:
682  Replace(user, return_value);
683  break;
684  case 1:
685  Replace(user, ctor_or_instance);
686  break;
687  default:
688  UNREACHABLE();
689  }
690  }
691  }
692  node->Kill();
693  return Replace(return_value);
694 }
695 
696 Reduction JSNativeContextSpecialization::ReduceJSInstanceOf(Node* node) {
697  JSInstanceOfNode n(node);
698  FeedbackParameter const& p = n.Parameters();
699  Node* object = n.left();
700  Node* constructor = n.right();
701  TNode<Object> context = n.context();
702  FrameState frame_state = n.frame_state();
703  Effect effect = n.effect();
704  Control control = n.control();
705 
706  // Check if the right hand side is a known {receiver}, or
707  // we have feedback from the InstanceOfIC.
708  OptionalJSObjectRef receiver;
709  HeapObjectMatcher m(constructor);
710  if (m.HasResolvedValue() && m.Ref(broker()).IsJSObject()) {
711  receiver = m.Ref(broker()).AsJSObject();
712  } else if (p.feedback().IsValid()) {
713  ProcessedFeedback const& feedback =
714  broker()->GetFeedbackForInstanceOf(FeedbackSource(p.feedback()));
715  if (feedback.IsInsufficient()) return NoChange();
716  receiver = feedback.AsInstanceOf().value();
717  } else {
718  return NoChange();
719  }
720 
721  if (!receiver.has_value()) return NoChange();
722 
723  MapRef receiver_map = receiver->map(broker());
724  NameRef name = broker()->has_instance_symbol();
725  PropertyAccessInfo access_info =
726  broker()->GetPropertyAccessInfo(receiver_map, name, AccessMode::kLoad);
727 
728  // TODO(v8:11457) Support dictionary mode holders here.
729  if (access_info.IsInvalid() || access_info.HasDictionaryHolder()) {
730  return NoChange();
731  }
732  access_info.RecordDependencies(dependencies());
733 
734  PropertyAccessBuilder access_builder(jsgraph(), broker());
735 
736  if (access_info.IsNotFound()) {
737  // If there's no @@hasInstance handler, the OrdinaryHasInstance operation
738  // takes over, but that requires the constructor to be callable.
739  if (!receiver_map.is_callable()) return NoChange();
740 
741  dependencies()->DependOnStablePrototypeChains(
742  access_info.lookup_start_object_maps(), kStartAtPrototype);
743 
744  // Monomorphic property access.
745  access_builder.BuildCheckMaps(constructor, &effect, control,
746  access_info.lookup_start_object_maps());
747 
748  // Lower to OrdinaryHasInstance(C, O).
749  NodeProperties::ReplaceValueInput(node, constructor, 0);
750  NodeProperties::ReplaceValueInput(node, object, 1);
751  NodeProperties::ReplaceEffectInput(node, effect);
752  static_assert(n.FeedbackVectorIndex() == 2);
753  node->RemoveInput(n.FeedbackVectorIndex());
754  NodeProperties::ChangeOp(node, javascript()->OrdinaryHasInstance());
755  return Changed(node).FollowedBy(ReduceJSOrdinaryHasInstance(node));
756  }
757 
758  if (access_info.IsFastDataConstant()) {
759  OptionalJSObjectRef holder = access_info.holder();
760  bool found_on_proto = holder.has_value();
761  JSObjectRef holder_ref = found_on_proto ? holder.value() : receiver.value();
762  if (access_info.field_representation().IsDouble()) return NoChange();
763  OptionalObjectRef constant = holder_ref.GetOwnFastConstantDataProperty(
764  broker(), access_info.field_representation(), access_info.field_index(),
765  dependencies());
766  if (!constant.has_value() || !constant->IsHeapObject() ||
767  !constant->AsHeapObject().map(broker()).is_callable()) {
768  return NoChange();
769  }
770 
771  if (found_on_proto) {
772  dependencies()->DependOnStablePrototypeChains(
773  access_info.lookup_start_object_maps(), kStartAtPrototype,
774  holder.value());
775  }
776 
777  // Check that {constructor} is actually {receiver}.
778  constructor = access_builder.BuildCheckValue(constructor, &effect, control,
779  *receiver);
780 
781  // Monomorphic property access.
782  access_builder.BuildCheckMaps(constructor, &effect, control,
783  access_info.lookup_start_object_maps());
784 
785  // Create a nested frame state inside the current method's most-recent frame
786  // state that will ensure that deopts that happen after this point will not
787  // fallback to the last Checkpoint--which would completely re-execute the
788  // instanceof logic--but rather create an activation of a version of the
789  // ToBoolean stub that finishes the remaining work of instanceof and returns
790  // to the caller without duplicating side-effects upon a lazy deopt.
791  Node* continuation_frame_state = CreateStubBuiltinContinuationFrameState(
792  jsgraph(), Builtin::kToBooleanLazyDeoptContinuation, context, nullptr,
793  0, frame_state, ContinuationFrameStateMode::LAZY);
794 
795  // Call the @@hasInstance handler.
796  Node* target = jsgraph()->ConstantNoHole(*constant, broker());
797  Node* feedback = jsgraph()->UndefinedConstant();
798  // Value inputs plus context, frame state, effect, control.
799  static_assert(JSCallNode::ArityForArgc(1) + 4 == 8);
800  node->EnsureInputCount(graph()->zone(), 8);
801  node->ReplaceInput(JSCallNode::TargetIndex(), target);
802  node->ReplaceInput(JSCallNode::ReceiverIndex(), constructor);
803  node->ReplaceInput(JSCallNode::ArgumentIndex(0), object);
804  node->ReplaceInput(3, feedback);
805  node->ReplaceInput(4, context);
806  node->ReplaceInput(5, continuation_frame_state);
807  node->ReplaceInput(6, effect);
808  node->ReplaceInput(7, control);
809  NodeProperties::ChangeOp(
810  node, javascript()->Call(JSCallNode::ArityForArgc(1), CallFrequency(),
811  FeedbackSource(),
812  ConvertReceiverMode::kNotNullOrUndefined));
813 
814  // Rewire the value uses of {node} to ToBoolean conversion of the result.
815  Node* value = graph()->NewNode(simplified()->ToBoolean(), node);
816  for (Edge edge : node->use_edges()) {
817  if (NodeProperties::IsValueEdge(edge) && edge.from() != value) {
818  edge.UpdateTo(value);
819  Revisit(edge.from());
820  }
821  }
822  return Changed(node);
823  }
824 
825  return NoChange();
826 }

828 JSNativeContextSpecialization::InferHasInPrototypeChainResult
829 JSNativeContextSpecialization::InferHasInPrototypeChain(
830  Node* receiver, Effect effect, HeapObjectRef prototype) {
831  ZoneRefSet<Map> receiver_maps;
832  NodeProperties::InferMapsResult result = NodeProperties::InferMapsUnsafe(
833  broker(), receiver, effect, &receiver_maps);
834  if (result == NodeProperties::kNoMaps) return kMayBeInPrototypeChain;
835 
836  ZoneVector<MapRef> receiver_map_refs(zone());
837 
838  // Try to determine either that all of the {receiver_maps} have the given
839  // {prototype} in their chain, or that none do. If we can't tell, return
840  // kMayBeInPrototypeChain.
841  bool all = true;
842  bool none = true;
843  for (MapRef map : receiver_maps) {
844  receiver_map_refs.push_back(map);
845  if (result == NodeProperties::kUnreliableMaps && !map.is_stable()) {
846  return kMayBeInPrototypeChain;
847  }
848  while (true) {
849  if (IsSpecialReceiverInstanceType(map.instance_type())) {
850  return kMayBeInPrototypeChain;
851  }
852  if (!map.IsJSObjectMap()) {
853  all = false;
854  break;
855  }
856  HeapObjectRef map_prototype = map.prototype(broker());
857  if (map_prototype.equals(prototype)) {
858  none = false;
859  break;
860  }
861  map = map_prototype.map(broker());
862  // TODO(v8:11457) Support dictionary mode protoypes here.
863  if (!map.is_stable() || map.is_dictionary_map()) {
864  return kMayBeInPrototypeChain;
865  }
866  if (map.oddball_type(broker()) == OddballType::kNull) {
867  all = false;
868  break;
869  }
870  }
871  }
872  DCHECK_IMPLIES(all, !none);
873  if (!all && !none) return kMayBeInPrototypeChain;
874 
875  {
876  OptionalJSObjectRef last_prototype;
877  if (all) {
878  // We don't need to protect the full chain if we found the prototype, we
879  // can stop at {prototype}. In fact we could stop at the one before
880  // {prototype} but since we're dealing with multiple receiver maps this
881  // might be a different object each time, so it's much simpler to include
882  // {prototype}. That does, however, mean that we must check {prototype}'s
883  // map stability.
884  if (!prototype.IsJSObject() || !prototype.map(broker()).is_stable()) {
885  return kMayBeInPrototypeChain;
886  }
887  last_prototype = prototype.AsJSObject();
888  }
889  WhereToStart start = result == NodeProperties::kUnreliableMaps
890  ? kStartAtReceiver
891  : kStartAtPrototype;
892  dependencies()->DependOnStablePrototypeChains(receiver_map_refs, start,
893  last_prototype);
894  }
895 
896  DCHECK_EQ(all, !none);
897  return all ? kIsInPrototypeChain : kIsNotInPrototypeChain;
898 }

900 Reduction JSNativeContextSpecialization::ReduceJSHasInPrototypeChain(
901  Node* node) {
902  DCHECK_EQ(IrOpcode::kJSHasInPrototypeChain, node->opcode());
903  Node* value = NodeProperties::GetValueInput(node, 0);
904  Node* prototype = NodeProperties::GetValueInput(node, 1);
905  Effect effect{NodeProperties::GetEffectInput(node)};
906 
907  // Check if we can constant-fold the prototype chain walk
908  // for the given {value} and the {prototype}.
909  HeapObjectMatcher m(prototype);
910  if (m.HasResolvedValue()) {
911  InferHasInPrototypeChainResult result =
912  InferHasInPrototypeChain(value, effect, m.Ref(broker()));
913  if (result != kMayBeInPrototypeChain) {
914  Node* result_in_chain =
915  jsgraph()->BooleanConstant(result == kIsInPrototypeChain);
916  ReplaceWithValue(node, result_in_chain);
917  return Replace(result_in_chain);
918  }
919  }
920 
921  return NoChange();
922 }

924 Reduction JSNativeContextSpecialization::ReduceJSOrdinaryHasInstance(
925  Node* node) {
926  DCHECK_EQ(IrOpcode::kJSOrdinaryHasInstance, node->opcode());
927  Node* constructor = NodeProperties::GetValueInput(node, 0);
928  Node* object = NodeProperties::GetValueInput(node, 1);
929 
930  // Check if the {constructor} is known at compile time.
931  HeapObjectMatcher m(constructor);
932  if (!m.HasResolvedValue()) return NoChange();
933 
934  if (m.Ref(broker()).IsJSBoundFunction()) {
935  // OrdinaryHasInstance on bound functions turns into a recursive invocation
936  // of the instanceof operator again.
937  JSBoundFunctionRef function = m.Ref(broker()).AsJSBoundFunction();
938  Node* feedback = jsgraph()->UndefinedConstant();
939  NodeProperties::ReplaceValueInput(node, object,
940  JSInstanceOfNode::LeftIndex());
941  NodeProperties::ReplaceValueInput(
942  node,
943  jsgraph()->ConstantNoHole(function.bound_target_function(broker()),
944  broker()),
945  JSInstanceOfNode::RightIndex());
946  node->InsertInput(zone(), JSInstanceOfNode::FeedbackVectorIndex(),
947  feedback);
948  NodeProperties::ChangeOp(node, javascript()->InstanceOf(FeedbackSource()));
949  return Changed(node).FollowedBy(ReduceJSInstanceOf(node));
950  }
951 
952  if (m.Ref(broker()).IsJSFunction()) {
953  // Optimize if we currently know the "prototype" property.
954 
955  JSFunctionRef function = m.Ref(broker()).AsJSFunction();
956 
957  // TODO(neis): Remove the has_prototype_slot condition once the broker is
958  // always enabled.
959  if (!function.map(broker()).has_prototype_slot() ||
960  !function.has_instance_prototype(broker()) ||
961  function.PrototypeRequiresRuntimeLookup(broker())) {
962  return NoChange();
963  }
964 
965  HeapObjectRef prototype =
966  dependencies()->DependOnPrototypeProperty(function);
967  Node* prototype_constant = jsgraph()->ConstantNoHole(prototype, broker());
968 
969  // Lower the {node} to JSHasInPrototypeChain.
970  NodeProperties::ReplaceValueInput(node, object, 0);
971  NodeProperties::ReplaceValueInput(node, prototype_constant, 1);
972  NodeProperties::ChangeOp(node, javascript()->HasInPrototypeChain());
973  return Changed(node).FollowedBy(ReduceJSHasInPrototypeChain(node));
974  }
975 
976  return NoChange();
977 }

979 // ES section #sec-promise-resolve
980 Reduction JSNativeContextSpecialization::ReduceJSPromiseResolve(Node* node) {
981  DCHECK_EQ(IrOpcode::kJSPromiseResolve, node->opcode());
982  Node* constructor = NodeProperties::GetValueInput(node, 0);
983  Node* value = NodeProperties::GetValueInput(node, 1);
984  Node* context = NodeProperties::GetContextInput(node);
985  FrameState frame_state{NodeProperties::GetFrameStateInput(node)};
986  Effect effect{NodeProperties::GetEffectInput(node)};
987  Control control{NodeProperties::GetControlInput(node)};
988 
989  // Check if the {constructor} is the %Promise% function.
990  HeapObjectMatcher m(constructor);
991  if (!m.HasResolvedValue() ||
992  !m.Ref(broker()).equals(native_context().promise_function(broker()))) {
993  return NoChange();
994  }
995 
996  // Only optimize if {value} cannot be a JSPromise.
997  MapInference inference(broker(), value, effect);
998  if (!inference.HaveMaps() ||
999  inference.AnyOfInstanceTypesAre(JS_PROMISE_TYPE)) {
1000  return NoChange();
1001  }
1002 
1003  if (!dependencies()->DependOnPromiseHookProtector()) return NoChange();
1004 
1005  // Create a %Promise% instance and resolve it with {value}.
1006  Node* promise = effect =
1007  graph()->NewNode(javascript()->CreatePromise(), context, effect);
1008 
1009  // Create a nested frame state inside the current method's most-recent
1010  // {frame_state} that will ensure that lazy deoptimizations at this
1011  // point will still return the {promise} instead of the result of the
1012  // ResolvePromise operation (which yields undefined).
1013  Node* parameters[] = {promise};
1014  frame_state = CreateStubBuiltinContinuationFrameState(
1015  jsgraph(), Builtin::kAsyncFunctionLazyDeoptContinuation, context,
1016  parameters, arraysize(parameters), frame_state,
1017  ContinuationFrameStateMode::LAZY);
1018 
1019  effect = graph()->NewNode(javascript()->ResolvePromise(), promise, value,
1020  context, frame_state, effect, control);
1021  ReplaceWithValue(node, promise, effect, control);
1022  return Replace(promise);
1023 }

1025 // ES section #sec-promise-resolve-functions
1026 Reduction JSNativeContextSpecialization::ReduceJSResolvePromise(Node* node) {
1027  DCHECK_EQ(IrOpcode::kJSResolvePromise, node->opcode());
1028  Node* promise = NodeProperties::GetValueInput(node, 0);
1029  Node* resolution = NodeProperties::GetValueInput(node, 1);
1030  Node* context = NodeProperties::GetContextInput(node);
1031  Effect effect{NodeProperties::GetEffectInput(node)};
1032  Control control{NodeProperties::GetControlInput(node)};
1033 
1034  // Check if we know something about the {resolution}.
1035  MapInference inference(broker(), resolution, effect);
1036  if (!inference.HaveMaps()) return NoChange();
1037  ZoneRefSet<Map> const& resolution_maps = inference.GetMaps();
1038 
1039  // Compute property access info for "then" on {resolution}.
1040  ZoneVector<PropertyAccessInfo> access_infos(graph()->zone());
1041  AccessInfoFactory access_info_factory(broker(), graph()->zone());
1042 
1043  for (MapRef map : resolution_maps) {
1044  access_infos.push_back(broker()->GetPropertyAccessInfo(
1045  map, broker()->then_string(), AccessMode::kLoad));
1046  }
1047  PropertyAccessInfo access_info =
1048  access_info_factory.FinalizePropertyAccessInfosAsOne(access_infos,
1049  AccessMode::kLoad);
1050 
1051  // TODO(v8:11457) Support dictionary mode prototypes here.
1052  if (access_info.IsInvalid() || access_info.HasDictionaryHolder()) {
1053  return inference.NoChange();
1054  }
1055 
1056  // Only optimize when {resolution} definitely doesn't have a "then" property.
1057  if (!access_info.IsNotFound()) return inference.NoChange();
1058 
1059  if (!inference.RelyOnMapsViaStability(dependencies())) {
1060  return inference.NoChange();
1061  }
1062 
1063  dependencies()->DependOnStablePrototypeChains(
1064  access_info.lookup_start_object_maps(), kStartAtPrototype);
1065 
1066  // Simply fulfill the {promise} with the {resolution}.
1067  Node* value = effect =
1068  graph()->NewNode(javascript()->FulfillPromise(), promise, resolution,
1069  context, effect, control);
1070  ReplaceWithValue(node, value, effect, control);
1071  return Replace(value);
1072 }

1093 // TODO(neis): Try to merge this with ReduceNamedAccess by introducing a new
1094 // PropertyAccessInfo kind for global accesses and using the existing mechanism
1095 // for building loads/stores.
1096 // Note: The "receiver" parameter is only used for DCHECKS, but that's on
1097 // purpose. This way we can assert the super property access cases won't hit the
1098 // code which hasn't been modified to support super property access.
1099 Reduction JSNativeContextSpecialization::ReduceGlobalAccess(
1100  Node* node, Node* lookup_start_object, Node* receiver, Node* value,
1101  NameRef name, AccessMode access_mode, Node* key,
1102  PropertyCellRef property_cell, Node* effect) {
1103  if (!property_cell.Cache(broker())) {
1104  TRACE_BROKER_MISSING(broker(), "usable data for " << property_cell);
1105  return NoChange();
1106  }
1107 
1108  ObjectRef property_cell_value = property_cell.value(broker());
1109  if (property_cell_value.IsPropertyCellHole()) {
1110  // The property cell is no longer valid.
1111  return NoChange();
1112  }
1113 
1114  PropertyDetails property_details = property_cell.property_details();
1115  PropertyCellType property_cell_type = property_details.cell_type();
1116  DCHECK_EQ(PropertyKind::kData, property_details.kind());
1117 
1118  Node* control = NodeProperties::GetControlInput(node);
1119  if (effect == nullptr) {
1120  effect = NodeProperties::GetEffectInput(node);
1121  }
1122 
1123  // We have additional constraints for stores.
1124  if (access_mode == AccessMode::kStore) {
1125  DCHECK_EQ(receiver, lookup_start_object);
1126  if (property_details.IsReadOnly()) {
1127  // Don't even bother trying to lower stores to read-only data properties.
1128  // TODO(neis): We could generate code that checks if the new value equals
1129  // the old one and then does nothing or deopts, respectively.
1130  return NoChange();
1131  } else if (property_cell_type == PropertyCellType::kUndefined) {
1132  return NoChange();
1133  } else if (property_cell_type == PropertyCellType::kConstantType) {
1134  // We rely on stability further below.
1135  if (property_cell_value.IsHeapObject() &&
1136  !property_cell_value.AsHeapObject().map(broker()).is_stable()) {
1137  return NoChange();
1138  }
1139  }
1140  } else if (access_mode == AccessMode::kHas) {
1141  DCHECK_EQ(receiver, lookup_start_object);
1142  // has checks cannot follow the fast-path used by loads when these
1143  // conditions hold.
1144  if ((property_details.IsConfigurable() || !property_details.IsReadOnly()) &&
1145  property_details.cell_type() != PropertyCellType::kConstant &&
1146  property_details.cell_type() != PropertyCellType::kUndefined)
1147  return NoChange();
1148  }
1149 
1150  // Ensure that {key} matches the specified {name} (if {key} is given).
1151  if (key != nullptr) {
1152  effect = BuildCheckEqualsName(name, key, effect, control);
1153  }
1154 
1155  // If we have a {lookup_start_object} to validate, we do so by checking that
1156  // its map is the (target) global proxy's map. This guarantees that in fact
1157  // the lookup start object is the global proxy.
1158  // Note: we rely on the map constant below being the same as what is used in
1159  // NativeContextRef::GlobalIsDetached().
1160  if (lookup_start_object != nullptr) {
1161  effect = graph()->NewNode(
1162  simplified()->CheckMaps(
1163  CheckMapsFlag::kNone,
1164  ZoneRefSet<Map>(
1165  native_context().global_proxy_object(broker()).map(broker()))),
1166  lookup_start_object, effect, control);
1167  }
1168 
1169  if (access_mode == AccessMode::kLoad || access_mode == AccessMode::kHas) {
1170  // Load from non-configurable, read-only data property on the global
1171  // object can be constant-folded, even without deoptimization support.
1172  if (!property_details.IsConfigurable() && property_details.IsReadOnly()) {
1173  value = access_mode == AccessMode::kHas
1174  ? jsgraph()->TrueConstant()
1175  : jsgraph()->ConstantNoHole(property_cell_value, broker());
1176  } else {
1177  // Record a code dependency on the cell if we can benefit from the
1178  // additional feedback, or the global property is configurable (i.e.
1179  // can be deleted or reconfigured to an accessor property).
1180  if (property_details.cell_type() != PropertyCellType::kMutable ||
1181  property_details.IsConfigurable()) {
1182  dependencies()->DependOnGlobalProperty(property_cell);
1183  }
1184 
1185  // Load from constant/undefined global property can be constant-folded.
1186  if (property_details.cell_type() == PropertyCellType::kConstant ||
1187  property_details.cell_type() == PropertyCellType::kUndefined) {
1188  value = access_mode == AccessMode::kHas
1189  ? jsgraph()->TrueConstant()
1190  : jsgraph()->ConstantNoHole(property_cell_value, broker());
1191  DCHECK(!property_cell_value.IsHeapObject() ||
1192  !property_cell_value.IsPropertyCellHole());
1193  } else {
1194  DCHECK_NE(AccessMode::kHas, access_mode);
1195 
1196  // Load from constant type cell can benefit from type feedback.
1197  OptionalMapRef map;
1198  Type property_cell_value_type = Type::NonInternal();
1199  MachineRepresentation representation = MachineRepresentation::kTagged;
1200  if (property_details.cell_type() == PropertyCellType::kConstantType) {
1201  // Compute proper type based on the current value in the cell.
1202  if (property_cell_value.IsSmi()) {
1203  property_cell_value_type = Type::SignedSmall();
1204  representation = MachineRepresentation::kTaggedSigned;
1205  } else if (property_cell_value.IsHeapNumber()) {
1206  property_cell_value_type = Type::Number();
1207  representation = MachineRepresentation::kTaggedPointer;
1208  } else {
1209  MapRef property_cell_value_map =
1210  property_cell_value.AsHeapObject().map(broker());
1211  property_cell_value_type =
1212  Type::For(property_cell_value_map, broker());
1213  representation = MachineRepresentation::kTaggedPointer;
1214 
1215  // We can only use the property cell value map for map check
1216  // elimination if it's stable, i.e. the HeapObject wasn't
1217  // mutated without the cell state being updated.
1218  if (property_cell_value_map.is_stable()) {
1219  dependencies()->DependOnStableMap(property_cell_value_map);
1220  map = property_cell_value_map;
1221  }
1222  }
1223  }
1224  value = effect = graph()->NewNode(
1225  simplified()->LoadField(ForPropertyCellValue(
1226  representation, property_cell_value_type, map, name)),
1227  jsgraph()->ConstantNoHole(property_cell, broker()), effect,
1228  control);
1229  }
1230  }
1231  } else if (access_mode == AccessMode::kStore) {
1232  DCHECK_EQ(receiver, lookup_start_object);
1233  DCHECK(!property_details.IsReadOnly());
1234  switch (property_details.cell_type()) {
1235  case PropertyCellType::kConstant: {
1236  // Record a code dependency on the cell, and just deoptimize if the new
1237  // value doesn't match the previous value stored inside the cell.
1238  dependencies()->DependOnGlobalProperty(property_cell);
1239  Node* check = graph()->NewNode(
1240  simplified()->ReferenceEqual(), value,
1241  jsgraph()->ConstantNoHole(property_cell_value, broker()));
1242  effect = graph()->NewNode(
1243  simplified()->CheckIf(DeoptimizeReason::kValueMismatch), check,
1244  effect, control);
1245  break;
1246  }
1247  case PropertyCellType::kConstantType: {
1248  // Record a code dependency on the cell, and just deoptimize if the new
1249  // value's type doesn't match the type of the previous value in the
1250  // cell.
1251  dependencies()->DependOnGlobalProperty(property_cell);
1252  Type property_cell_value_type;
1253  MachineRepresentation representation = MachineRepresentation::kTagged;
1254  if (property_cell_value.IsHeapObject()) {
1255  MapRef property_cell_value_map =
1256  property_cell_value.AsHeapObject().map(broker());
1257  dependencies()->DependOnStableMap(property_cell_value_map);
1258 
1259  // Check that the {value} is a HeapObject.
1260  value = effect = graph()->NewNode(simplified()->CheckHeapObject(),
1261  value, effect, control);
1262  // Check {value} map against the {property_cell_value} map.
1263  effect = graph()->NewNode(
1264  simplified()->CheckMaps(CheckMapsFlag::kNone,
1265  ZoneRefSet<Map>(property_cell_value_map)),
1266  value, effect, control);
1267  property_cell_value_type = Type::OtherInternal();
1268  representation = MachineRepresentation::kTaggedPointer;
1269  } else {
1270  // Check that the {value} is a Smi.
1271  value = effect = graph()->NewNode(
1272  simplified()->CheckSmi(FeedbackSource()), value, effect, control);
1273  property_cell_value_type = Type::SignedSmall();
1274  representation = MachineRepresentation::kTaggedSigned;
1275  }
1276  effect =
1277  graph()->NewNode(simplified()->StoreField(ForPropertyCellValue(
1278  representation, property_cell_value_type,
1279  OptionalMapRef(), name)),
1280  jsgraph()->ConstantNoHole(property_cell, broker()),
1281  value, effect, control);
1282  break;
1283  }
1284  case PropertyCellType::kMutable: {
1285  // Record a code dependency on the cell, and just deoptimize if the
1286  // property ever becomes read-only.
1287  dependencies()->DependOnGlobalProperty(property_cell);
1288  effect =
1289  graph()->NewNode(simplified()->StoreField(ForPropertyCellValue(
1290  MachineRepresentation::kTagged,
1291  Type::NonInternal(), OptionalMapRef(), name)),
1292  jsgraph()->ConstantNoHole(property_cell, broker()),
1293  value, effect, control);
1294  break;
1295  }
1296  case PropertyCellType::kUndefined:
1297  case PropertyCellType::kInTransition:
1298  UNREACHABLE();
1299  }
1300  } else {
1301  return NoChange();
1302  }
1303 
1304  ReplaceWithValue(node, value, effect, control);
1305  return Replace(value);
1306 }

1308 Reduction JSNativeContextSpecialization::ReduceJSLoadGlobal(Node* node) {
1309  JSLoadGlobalNode n(node);
1310  LoadGlobalParameters const& p = n.Parameters();
1311  if (!p.feedback().IsValid()) return NoChange();
1312 
1313  ProcessedFeedback const& processed =
1314  broker()->GetFeedbackForGlobalAccess(FeedbackSource(p.feedback()));
1315  if (processed.IsInsufficient()) return NoChange();
1316 
1317  GlobalAccessFeedback const& feedback = processed.AsGlobalAccess();
1318  if (feedback.IsScriptContextSlot()) {
1319  Effect effect = n.effect();
1320  Control control = n.control();
1321  Node* script_context =
1322  jsgraph()->ConstantNoHole(feedback.script_context(), broker());
1323  Node* value;
1324  if (v8_flags.script_context_cells && !feedback.immutable()) {
1325  // We collect feedback only for mutable context slots.
1326  value = effect = control =
1327  graph()->NewNode(javascript()->LoadContext(0, feedback.slot_index()),
1328  script_context, effect, control);
1329  } else {
1330  value = effect =
1331  graph()->NewNode(javascript()->LoadContextNoCell(
1332  0, feedback.slot_index(), feedback.immutable()),
1333  script_context, effect);
1334  }
1335  ReplaceWithValue(node, value, effect, control);
1336  return Replace(value);
1337  } else if (feedback.IsPropertyCell()) {
1338  return ReduceGlobalAccess(node, nullptr, nullptr, nullptr, p.name(),
1339  AccessMode::kLoad, nullptr,
1340  feedback.property_cell());
1341  } else {
1342  DCHECK(feedback.IsMegamorphic());
1343  return NoChange();
1344  }
1345 }

1347 Reduction JSNativeContextSpecialization::ReduceJSStoreGlobal(Node* node) {
1348  JSStoreGlobalNode n(node);
1349  StoreGlobalParameters const& p = n.Parameters();
1350  Node* value = n.value();
1351  if (!p.feedback().IsValid()) return NoChange();
1352 
1353  ProcessedFeedback const& processed =
1354  broker()->GetFeedbackForGlobalAccess(FeedbackSource(p.feedback()));
1355  if (processed.IsInsufficient()) return NoChange();
1356 
1357  GlobalAccessFeedback const& feedback = processed.AsGlobalAccess();
1358  if (feedback.IsScriptContextSlot()) {
1359  if (feedback.immutable()) return NoChange();
1360  Node* effect = n.effect();
1361  Node* control = n.control();
1362  Node* frame_state = n.frame_state();
1363  Node* script_context =
1364  jsgraph()->ConstantNoHole(feedback.script_context(), broker());
1365  if (v8_flags.script_context_cells) {
1366  effect = control =
1367  graph()->NewNode(javascript()->StoreContext(0, feedback.slot_index()),
1368  value, script_context, frame_state, effect, control);
1369  } else {
1370  effect = graph()->NewNode(
1371  javascript()->StoreContextNoCell(0, feedback.slot_index()), value,
1372  script_context, effect, control);
1373  }
1374  ReplaceWithValue(node, value, effect, control);
1375  return Replace(value);
1376  } else if (feedback.IsPropertyCell()) {
1377  return ReduceGlobalAccess(node, nullptr, nullptr, value, p.name(),
1378  AccessMode::kStore, nullptr,
1379  feedback.property_cell());
1380  } else {
1381  DCHECK(feedback.IsMegamorphic());
1382  return NoChange();
1383  }
1384 }

1386 Reduction JSNativeContextSpecialization::ReduceMegaDOMPropertyAccess(
1387  Node* node, Node* value, MegaDOMPropertyAccessFeedback const& feedback,
1388  FeedbackSource const& source) {
1389  DCHECK(node->opcode() == IrOpcode::kJSLoadNamed ||
1390  node->opcode() == IrOpcode::kJSLoadProperty);
1391  // TODO(mslekova): Add support and tests for kJSLoadNamedFromSuper.
1392  static_assert(JSLoadNamedNode::ObjectIndex() == 0 &&
1393  JSLoadPropertyNode::ObjectIndex() == 0,
1394  "Assumptions about ObjectIndex have changed, please update "
1395  "this function.");
1396 
1397  Node* effect = NodeProperties::GetEffectInput(node);
1398  Node* control = NodeProperties::GetControlInput(node);
1399  Node* frame_state = NodeProperties::GetFrameStateInput(node);
1400 
1401  Node* lookup_start_object = NodeProperties::GetValueInput(node, 0);
1402 
1403  if (!dependencies()->DependOnMegaDOMProtector()) {
1404  return NoChange();
1405  }
1406 
1407  FunctionTemplateInfoRef function_template_info = feedback.info();
1408  int16_t range_start =
1409  function_template_info.allowed_receiver_instance_type_range_start();
1410  int16_t range_end =
1411  function_template_info.allowed_receiver_instance_type_range_end();
1412  DCHECK_IMPLIES(range_start == 0, range_end == 0);
1413  DCHECK_LE(range_start, range_end);
1414 
1415  // TODO(mslekova): This could be a new InstanceTypeCheck operator
1416  // that gets lowered later on (e.g. during generic lowering).
1417  Node* receiver_map = effect =
1418  graph()->NewNode(simplified()->LoadField(AccessBuilder::ForMap()),
1419  lookup_start_object, effect, control);
1420  Node* receiver_instance_type = effect = graph()->NewNode(
1421  simplified()->LoadField(AccessBuilder::ForMapInstanceType()),
1422  receiver_map, effect, control);
1423 
1424  if (v8_flags.experimental_embedder_instance_types && range_start != 0) {
1425  // Embedder instance ID is set, doing a simple range check.
1426  Node* diff_to_start =
1427  graph()->NewNode(simplified()->NumberSubtract(), receiver_instance_type,
1428  jsgraph()->ConstantNoHole(range_start));
1429  Node* range_length = jsgraph()->ConstantNoHole(range_end - range_start);
1430 
1431  // TODO(mslekova): Once we have the InstanceTypeCheck operator, we could
1432  // lower it to Uint32LessThan later on to perform what is done in bounds.h.
1433  Node* check = graph()->NewNode(simplified()->NumberLessThanOrEqual(),
1434  diff_to_start, range_length);
1435  effect = graph()->NewNode(
1436  simplified()->CheckIf(DeoptimizeReason::kWrongInstanceType), check,
1437  effect, control);
1438  } else if (function_template_info.is_signature_undefined(broker())) {
1439  // Signature is undefined, enough to check if the receiver is a JSApiObject.
1440  Node* check =
1441  graph()->NewNode(simplified()->NumberEqual(), receiver_instance_type,
1442  jsgraph()->ConstantNoHole(JS_API_OBJECT_TYPE));
1443  effect = graph()->NewNode(
1444  simplified()->CheckIf(DeoptimizeReason::kWrongInstanceType), check,
1445  effect, control);
1446  } else {
1447  // Calling out to builtin to do signature check.
1448  Callable callable = Builtins::CallableFor(
1449  isolate(), Builtin::kCallFunctionTemplate_CheckCompatibleReceiver);
1450  int stack_arg_count = callable.descriptor().GetStackParameterCount() +
1451  1 /* implicit receiver */;
1452 
1453  CallDescriptor* call_descriptor = Linkage::GetStubCallDescriptor(
1454  graph()->zone(), callable.descriptor(), stack_arg_count,
1455  CallDescriptor::kNeedsFrameState, Operator::kNoProperties);
1456 
1457  Node* inputs[8] = {
1458  jsgraph()->HeapConstantNoHole(callable.code()),
1459  jsgraph()->ConstantNoHole(function_template_info, broker()),
1460  jsgraph()->Int32Constant(stack_arg_count),
1461  lookup_start_object,
1462  jsgraph()->ConstantNoHole(native_context(), broker()),
1463  frame_state,
1464  effect,
1465  control};
1466 
1467  value = effect = control =
1468  graph()->NewNode(common()->Call(call_descriptor), 8, inputs);
1469  return Replace(value);
1470  }
1471 
1472  value = InlineApiCall(lookup_start_object, frame_state, nullptr /*value*/,
1473  &effect, &control, function_template_info, source);
1474  ReplaceWithValue(node, value, effect, control);
1475  return Replace(value);
1476 }

1478 Reduction JSNativeContextSpecialization::ReduceNamedAccess(
1479  Node* node, Node* value, NamedAccessFeedback const& feedback,
1480  AccessMode access_mode, Node* key) {
1481  DCHECK(node->opcode() == IrOpcode::kJSLoadNamed ||
1482  node->opcode() == IrOpcode::kJSSetNamedProperty ||
1483  node->opcode() == IrOpcode::kJSLoadProperty ||
1484  node->opcode() == IrOpcode::kJSSetKeyedProperty ||
1485  node->opcode() == IrOpcode::kJSDefineNamedOwnProperty ||
1486  node->opcode() == IrOpcode::kJSDefineKeyedOwnPropertyInLiteral ||
1487  node->opcode() == IrOpcode::kJSHasProperty ||
1488  node->opcode() == IrOpcode::kJSLoadNamedFromSuper ||
1489  node->opcode() == IrOpcode::kJSDefineKeyedOwnProperty);
1490  static_assert(JSLoadNamedNode::ObjectIndex() == 0 &&
1491  JSSetNamedPropertyNode::ObjectIndex() == 0 &&
1492  JSLoadPropertyNode::ObjectIndex() == 0 &&
1493  JSSetKeyedPropertyNode::ObjectIndex() == 0 &&
1494  JSDefineNamedOwnPropertyNode::ObjectIndex() == 0 &&
1495  JSSetNamedPropertyNode::ObjectIndex() == 0 &&
1496  JSDefineKeyedOwnPropertyInLiteralNode::ObjectIndex() == 0 &&
1497  JSHasPropertyNode::ObjectIndex() == 0 &&
1498  JSDefineKeyedOwnPropertyNode::ObjectIndex() == 0);
1499  static_assert(JSLoadNamedFromSuperNode::ReceiverIndex() == 0);
1500 
1501  Node* context = NodeProperties::GetContextInput(node);
1502  FrameState frame_state{NodeProperties::GetFrameStateInput(node)};
1503  Effect effect{NodeProperties::GetEffectInput(node)};
1504  Control control{NodeProperties::GetControlInput(node)};
1505 
1506  // receiver = the object we pass to the accessor (if any) as the "this" value.
1507  Node* receiver = NodeProperties::GetValueInput(node, 0);
1508  // lookup_start_object = the object where we start looking for the property.
1509  Node* lookup_start_object;
1510  if (node->opcode() == IrOpcode::kJSLoadNamedFromSuper) {
1511  DCHECK(v8_flags.super_ic);
1512  JSLoadNamedFromSuperNode n(node);
1513  // Lookup start object is the __proto__ of the home object.
1514  lookup_start_object = effect =
1515  BuildLoadPrototypeFromObject(n.home_object(), effect, control);
1516  } else {
1517  lookup_start_object = receiver;
1518  }
1519 
1520  // Either infer maps from the graph or use the feedback.
1521  ZoneVector<MapRef> inferred_maps(zone());
1522  if (!InferMaps(lookup_start_object, effect, &inferred_maps)) {
1523  for (MapRef map : feedback.maps()) {
1524  inferred_maps.push_back(map);
1525  }
1526  }
1527  RemoveImpossibleMaps(lookup_start_object, &inferred_maps);
1528 
1529  // Check if we have an access o.x or o.x=v where o is the target native
1530  // contexts' global proxy, and turn that into a direct access to the
1531  // corresponding global object instead.
1532  if (inferred_maps.size() == 1) {
1533  MapRef lookup_start_object_map = inferred_maps[0];
1534  if (lookup_start_object_map.equals(
1535  native_context().global_proxy_object(broker()).map(broker()))) {
1536  if (!native_context().GlobalIsDetached(broker())) {
1537  OptionalPropertyCellRef cell =
1538  native_context().global_object(broker()).GetPropertyCell(
1539  broker(), feedback.name());
1540  if (!cell.has_value()) return NoChange();
1541  // Note: The map check generated by ReduceGlobalAccesses ensures that we
1542  // will deopt when/if GlobalIsDetached becomes true.
1543  return ReduceGlobalAccess(node, lookup_start_object, receiver, value,
1544  feedback.name(), access_mode, key, *cell,
1545  effect);
1546  }
1547  }
1548  }
1549 
1550  ZoneVector<PropertyAccessInfo> access_infos(zone());
1551  {
1552  ZoneVector<PropertyAccessInfo> access_infos_for_feedback(zone());
1553  for (MapRef map : inferred_maps) {
1554  if (map.is_deprecated()) continue;
1555 
1556  // TODO(v8:12547): Support writing to objects in shared space, which need
1557  // a write barrier that calls Object::Share to ensure the RHS is shared.
1558  if (InstanceTypeChecker::IsAlwaysSharedSpaceJSObject(
1559  map.instance_type()) &&
1560  access_mode == AccessMode::kStore) {
1561  return NoChange();
1562  }
1563 
1564  PropertyAccessInfo access_info =
1565  broker()->GetPropertyAccessInfo(map, feedback.name(), access_mode);
1566  access_infos_for_feedback.push_back(access_info);
1567  }
1568 
1569  AccessInfoFactory access_info_factory(broker(), graph()->zone());
1570  if (!access_info_factory.FinalizePropertyAccessInfos(
1571  access_infos_for_feedback, access_mode, &access_infos)) {
1572  return NoChange();
1573  }
1574  }
1575 
1576  // Ensure that {key} matches the specified name (if {key} is given).
1577  if (key != nullptr) {
1578  effect = BuildCheckEqualsName(feedback.name(), key, effect, control);
1579  }
1580 
1581  // Collect call nodes to rewire exception edges.
1582  ZoneVector<Node*> if_exception_nodes(zone());
1583  ZoneVector<Node*>* if_exceptions = nullptr;
1584  Node* if_exception = nullptr;
1585  if (NodeProperties::IsExceptionalCall(node, &if_exception)) {
1586  if_exceptions = &if_exception_nodes;
1587  }
1588 
1589  PropertyAccessBuilder access_builder(jsgraph(), broker());
1590 
1591  // Check for the monomorphic cases.
1592  if (access_infos.size() == 1) {
1593  const PropertyAccessInfo& access_info = access_infos.front();
1594  if (receiver != lookup_start_object) {
1595  // Super property access. lookup_start_object is a JSReceiver or
1596  // null. It can't be a number, a string etc. So trying to build the
1597  // checks in the "else if" branch doesn't make sense.
1598 
1599  access_builder.BuildCheckMaps(
1600  lookup_start_object, &effect, control,
1601  access_info.lookup_start_object_maps(),
1602  feedback.has_deprecated_map_without_migration_target());
1603 
1604  if (HasOnlyStringWrapperMaps(broker(),
1605  access_info.lookup_start_object_maps())) {
1606  // In order to be able to use StringWrapperLength, we need a TypeGuard
1607  // when all input maps are StringWrapper maps.
1608  lookup_start_object = effect =
1609  graph()->NewNode(common()->TypeGuard(Type::StringWrapper()),
1610  lookup_start_object, effect, control);
1611  } else if (HasOnlyNonResizableTypedArrayMaps(
1612  broker(), access_info.lookup_start_object_maps())) {
1613  // In order to be able to use TypedArrayLength, we need a TypeGuard
1614  // when all input maps are TypedArray maps. We need this only when
1615  // all maps are non-RAB/GSAB maps, since TypedArrayLength only handles
1616  // non-RAB/GSAB maps.
1617  lookup_start_object = effect =
1618  graph()->NewNode(common()->TypeGuard(Type::TypedArray()),
1619  lookup_start_object, effect, control);
1620  }
1621 
1622  } else if (!access_builder.TryBuildStringCheck(
1623  broker(), access_info.lookup_start_object_maps(), &receiver,
1624  &effect, control) &&
1625  !access_builder.TryBuildNumberCheck(
1626  broker(), access_info.lookup_start_object_maps(), &receiver,
1627  &effect, control)) {
1628  // Try to build string check or number check if possible. Otherwise build
1629  // a map check.
1630 
1631  // TryBuildStringCheck and TryBuildNumberCheck don't update the receiver
1632  // if they fail.
1633  DCHECK_EQ(receiver, lookup_start_object);
1634  if (HasNumberMaps(broker(), access_info.lookup_start_object_maps())) {
1635  // We need to also let Smi {receiver}s through in this case, so
1636  // we construct a diamond, guarded by the Sminess of the {receiver}
1637  // and if {receiver} is not a Smi just emit a sequence of map checks.
1638  Node* check = graph()->NewNode(simplified()->ObjectIsSmi(), receiver);
1639  Node* branch = graph()->NewNode(common()->Branch(), check, control);
1640 
1641  Node* if_true = graph()->NewNode(common()->IfTrue(), branch);
1642  Node* etrue = effect;
1643 
1644  Control if_false{graph()->NewNode(common()->IfFalse(), branch)};
1645  Effect efalse = effect;
1646  access_builder.BuildCheckMaps(
1647  receiver, &efalse, if_false, access_info.lookup_start_object_maps(),
1648  feedback.has_deprecated_map_without_migration_target());
1649 
1650  control = graph()->NewNode(common()->Merge(2), if_true, if_false);
1651  effect =
1652  graph()->NewNode(common()->EffectPhi(2), etrue, efalse, control);
1653  } else {
1654  access_builder.BuildCheckMaps(
1655  receiver, &effect, control, access_info.lookup_start_object_maps(),
1656  feedback.has_deprecated_map_without_migration_target());
1657  }
1658 
1659  if (HasOnlyStringWrapperMaps(broker(),
1660  access_info.lookup_start_object_maps())) {
1661  // In order to be able to use StringWrapperLength, we need a TypeGuard
1662  // when all input maps are StringWrapper maps. Note that, alternatively,
1663  // we could have a CheckStringWrapper, but it makes things simpler to
1664  // just rely on CheckMaps. This is slightly suboptimal in case the code
1665  // contains multiple string wrappers with different properties, but this
1666  // should be a rare case.
1667  lookup_start_object = receiver = effect =
1668  graph()->NewNode(common()->TypeGuard(Type::StringWrapper()),
1669  lookup_start_object, effect, control);
1670  } else if (HasOnlyNonResizableTypedArrayMaps(
1671  broker(), access_info.lookup_start_object_maps())) {
1672  // In order to be able to use TypedArrayLength, we need a TypeGuard
1673  // when all input maps are TypedArray maps. We need this only when
1674  // all maps are non-RAB/GSAB maps, since TypedArrayLength only handles
1675  // non-RAB/GSAB maps.
1676  lookup_start_object = receiver = effect =
1677  graph()->NewNode(common()->TypeGuard(Type::TypedArray()),
1678  lookup_start_object, effect, control);
1679  }
1680  } else {
1681  // At least one of TryBuildStringCheck & TryBuildNumberCheck succeeded
1682  // and updated the receiver. Update lookup_start_object to match (they
1683  // should be the same).
1684  lookup_start_object = receiver;
1685  }
1686 
1687  // Generate the actual property access.
1688  std::optional<ValueEffectControl> continuation = BuildPropertyAccess(
1689  lookup_start_object, receiver, value, context, frame_state, effect,
1690  control, feedback.name(), if_exceptions, access_info, access_mode);
1691  if (!continuation) {
1692  // At this point we maybe have added nodes into the graph (e.g. via
1693  // NewNode or BuildCheckMaps) in some cases but we haven't connected them
1694  // to End since we haven't called ReplaceWithValue. Since they are nodes
1695  // which are not connected with End, they will be removed by graph
1696  // trimming.
1697  return NoChange();
1698  }
1699  value = continuation->value();
1700  effect = continuation->effect();
1701  control = continuation->control();
1702  } else {
1703  // The final states for every polymorphic branch. We join them with
1704  // Merge+Phi+EffectPhi at the bottom.
1705  ZoneVector<Node*> values(zone());
1706  ZoneVector<Node*> effects(zone());
1707  ZoneVector<Node*> controls(zone());
1708 
1709  Node* receiverissmi_control = nullptr;
1710  Node* receiverissmi_effect = effect;
1711 
1712  if (receiver == lookup_start_object) {
1713  // Check if {receiver} may be a number.
1714  bool receiverissmi_possible = false;
1715  for (PropertyAccessInfo const& access_info : access_infos) {
1716  if (HasNumberMaps(broker(), access_info.lookup_start_object_maps())) {
1717  receiverissmi_possible = true;
1718  break;
1719  }
1720  }
1721 
1722  // Handle the case that {receiver} may be a number.
1723  if (receiverissmi_possible) {
1724  Node* check = graph()->NewNode(simplified()->ObjectIsSmi(), receiver);
1725  Node* branch = graph()->NewNode(common()->Branch(), check, control);
1726  control = graph()->NewNode(common()->IfFalse(), branch);
1727  receiverissmi_control = graph()->NewNode(common()->IfTrue(), branch);
1728  receiverissmi_effect = effect;
1729  }
1730  }
1731 
1732  // Generate code for the various different property access patterns.
1733  Node* fallthrough_control = control;
1734  for (size_t j = 0; j < access_infos.size(); ++j) {
1735  PropertyAccessInfo const& access_info = access_infos[j];
1736  Node* this_value = value;
1737  Node* this_lookup_start_object = lookup_start_object;
1738  Node* this_receiver = receiver;
1739  Effect this_effect = effect;
1740  Control this_control{fallthrough_control};
1741 
1742  // Perform map check on {lookup_start_object}.
1743  ZoneVector<MapRef> const& lookup_start_object_maps =
1744  access_info.lookup_start_object_maps();
1745  {
1746  // Whether to insert a dedicated MapGuard node into the
1747  // effect to be able to learn from the control flow.
1748  bool insert_map_guard = true;
1749 
1750  // Check maps for the {lookup_start_object}s.
1751  if (j == access_infos.size() - 1) {
1752  // Last map check on the fallthrough control path, do a
1753  // conditional eager deoptimization exit here.
1754  access_builder.BuildCheckMaps(
1755  lookup_start_object, &this_effect, this_control,
1756  lookup_start_object_maps,
1757  feedback.has_deprecated_map_without_migration_target());
1758  fallthrough_control = nullptr;
1759 
1760  // Don't insert a MapGuard in this case, as the CheckMaps
1761  // node already gives you all the information you need
1762  // along the effect chain.
1763  insert_map_guard = false;
1764  } else {
1765  // Explicitly branch on the {lookup_start_object_maps}.
1766  ZoneRefSet<Map> maps(lookup_start_object_maps.begin(),
1767  lookup_start_object_maps.end(), graph()->zone());
1768  Node* check = this_effect =
1769  graph()->NewNode(simplified()->CompareMaps(maps),
1770  lookup_start_object, this_effect, this_control);
1771  Node* branch =
1772  graph()->NewNode(common()->Branch(), check, this_control);
1773  fallthrough_control = graph()->NewNode(common()->IfFalse(), branch);
1774  this_control = graph()->NewNode(common()->IfTrue(), branch);
1775  }
1776 
1777  // The Number case requires special treatment to also deal with Smis.
1778  if (HasNumberMaps(broker(), lookup_start_object_maps)) {
1779  // Join this check with the "receiver is smi" check above.
1780  DCHECK_EQ(receiver, lookup_start_object);
1781  DCHECK_NOT_NULL(receiverissmi_effect);
1782  DCHECK_NOT_NULL(receiverissmi_control);
1783  this_control = graph()->NewNode(common()->Merge(2), this_control,
1784  receiverissmi_control);
1785  this_effect = graph()->NewNode(common()->EffectPhi(2), this_effect,
1786  receiverissmi_effect, this_control);
1787  receiverissmi_effect = receiverissmi_control = nullptr;
1788 
1789  // The {lookup_start_object} can also be a Smi in this case, so
1790  // a MapGuard doesn't make sense for this at all.
1791  insert_map_guard = false;
1792  }
1793 
1794  // Introduce a MapGuard to learn from this on the effect chain.
1795  if (insert_map_guard) {
1796  ZoneRefSet<Map> maps(lookup_start_object_maps.begin(),
1797  lookup_start_object_maps.end(), graph()->zone());
1798  this_effect =
1799  graph()->NewNode(simplified()->MapGuard(maps),
1800  lookup_start_object, this_effect, this_control);
1801  }
1802 
1803  // If all {lookup_start_object_maps} are Strings we also need to rename
1804  // the {lookup_start_object} here to make sure that TurboFan knows that
1805  // along this path the {this_lookup_start_object} is a String. This is
1806  // because we want strict checking of types, for example for
1807  // StringLength operators.
1808  if (HasOnlyStringMaps(broker(), lookup_start_object_maps)) {
1809  DCHECK_EQ(receiver, lookup_start_object);
1810  this_lookup_start_object = this_receiver = this_effect =
1811  graph()->NewNode(common()->TypeGuard(Type::String()),
1812  lookup_start_object, this_effect, this_control);
1813  } else if (HasOnlyStringWrapperMaps(broker(),
1814  lookup_start_object_maps)) {
1815  bool receiver_is_lookup_start =
1816  this_lookup_start_object == this_receiver;
1817  DCHECK_IMPLIES(access_mode != AccessMode::kLoad,
1818  receiver_is_lookup_start);
1819  this_lookup_start_object = this_effect =
1820  graph()->NewNode(common()->TypeGuard(Type::StringWrapper()),
1821  lookup_start_object, this_effect, this_control);
1822  if (receiver_is_lookup_start) {
1823  this_receiver = this_lookup_start_object;
1824  }
1825  } else if (HasOnlyNonResizableTypedArrayMaps(
1826  broker(), lookup_start_object_maps)) {
1827  bool receiver_is_lookup_start =
1828  this_lookup_start_object == this_receiver;
1829  DCHECK_IMPLIES(access_mode != AccessMode::kLoad,
1830  receiver_is_lookup_start);
1831  this_lookup_start_object = this_effect =
1832  graph()->NewNode(common()->TypeGuard(Type::TypedArray()),
1833  lookup_start_object, this_effect, this_control);
1834  if (receiver_is_lookup_start) {
1835  this_receiver = this_lookup_start_object;
1836  }
1837  }
1838  }
1839 
1840  // Generate the actual property access.
1841  std::optional<ValueEffectControl> continuation = BuildPropertyAccess(
1842  this_lookup_start_object, this_receiver, this_value, context,
1843  frame_state, this_effect, this_control, feedback.name(),
1844  if_exceptions, access_info, access_mode);
1845  if (!continuation) {
1846  // At this point we maybe have added nodes into the graph (e.g. via
1847  // NewNode or BuildCheckMaps) in some cases but we haven't connected
1848  // them to End since we haven't called ReplaceWithValue. Since they are
1849  // nodes which are not connected with End, they will be removed by graph
1850  // trimming.
1851  return NoChange();
1852  }
1853 
1854  values.push_back(continuation->value());
1855  effects.push_back(continuation->effect());
1856  controls.push_back(continuation->control());
1857  }
1858 
1859  DCHECK_NULL(fallthrough_control);
1860 
1861  // Generate the final merge point for all (polymorphic) branches.
1862  int const control_count = static_cast<int>(controls.size());
1863  if (control_count == 0) {
1864  value = effect = control = jsgraph()->Dead();
1865  } else if (control_count == 1) {
1866  value = values.front();
1867  effect = effects.front();
1868  control = controls.front();
1869  } else {
1870  control = graph()->NewNode(common()->Merge(control_count), control_count,
1871  &controls.front());
1872  values.push_back(control);
1873  value = graph()->NewNode(
1874  common()->Phi(MachineRepresentation::kTagged, control_count),
1875  control_count + 1, &values.front());
1876  effects.push_back(control);
1877  effect = graph()->NewNode(common()->EffectPhi(control_count),
1878  control_count + 1, &effects.front());
1879  }
1880  }
1881 
1882  // Properly rewire IfException edges if {node} is inside a try-block.
1883  if (!if_exception_nodes.empty()) {
1884  DCHECK_NOT_NULL(if_exception);
1885  DCHECK_EQ(if_exceptions, &if_exception_nodes);
1886  int const if_exception_count = static_cast<int>(if_exceptions->size());
1887  Node* merge = graph()->NewNode(common()->Merge(if_exception_count),
1888  if_exception_count, &if_exceptions->front());
1889  if_exceptions->push_back(merge);
1890  Node* ephi =
1891  graph()->NewNode(common()->EffectPhi(if_exception_count),
1892  if_exception_count + 1, &if_exceptions->front());
1893  Node* phi = graph()->NewNode(
1894  common()->Phi(MachineRepresentation::kTagged, if_exception_count),
1895  if_exception_count + 1, &if_exceptions->front());
1896  ReplaceWithValue(if_exception, phi, ephi, merge);
1897  }
1898 
1899  ReplaceWithValue(node, value, effect, control);
1900  return Replace(value);
1901 }
