1903 Reduction JSNativeContextSpecialization::ReduceJSLoadNamed(Node* node) {
1904  JSLoadNamedNode n(node);
1905  NamedAccess const& p = n.Parameters();
1906  Node* const receiver = n.object();
1907  NameRef name = p.name();
1908 
1909  // Check if we have a constant receiver.
1910  HeapObjectMatcher m(receiver);
1911  if (m.HasResolvedValue()) {
1912  ObjectRef object = m.Ref(broker());
1913  if (object.IsJSFunction() && name.equals(broker()->prototype_string())) {
1914  // Optimize "prototype" property of functions.
1915  JSFunctionRef function = object.AsJSFunction();
1916  // TODO(neis): Remove the has_prototype_slot condition once the broker is
1917  // always enabled.
1918  if (!function.map(broker()).has_prototype_slot() ||
1919  !function.has_instance_prototype(broker()) ||
1920  function.PrototypeRequiresRuntimeLookup(broker())) {
1921  return NoChange();
1922  }
1923  HeapObjectRef prototype =
1924  dependencies()->DependOnPrototypeProperty(function);
1925  Node* value = jsgraph()->ConstantNoHole(prototype, broker());
1926  ReplaceWithValue(node, value);
1927  return Replace(value);
1928  } else if (object.IsString() && name.equals(broker()->length_string())) {
1929  // Constant-fold "length" property on constant strings.
1930  Node* value = jsgraph()->ConstantNoHole(object.AsString().length());
1931  ReplaceWithValue(node, value);
1932  return Replace(value);
1933  }
1934  }
1935 
1936  if (!p.feedback().IsValid()) return NoChange();
1937  return ReducePropertyAccess(node, nullptr, name, jsgraph()->Dead(),
1938  FeedbackSource(p.feedback()), AccessMode::kLoad);
1939 }

1952 Reduction JSNativeContextSpecialization::ReduceJSGetIterator(Node* node) {
1953  JSGetIteratorNode n(node);
1954  GetIteratorParameters const& p = n.Parameters();
1955 
1956  TNode<Object> receiver = n.receiver();
1957  TNode<Object> context = n.context();
1958  FrameState frame_state = n.frame_state();
1959  Effect effect = n.effect();
1960  Control control = n.control();
1961 
1962  Node* iterator_exception_node = nullptr;
1963  Node* if_exception_merge = nullptr;
1964  Node* if_exception_effect_phi = nullptr;
1965  Node* if_exception_phi = nullptr;
1966  bool has_exception_node =
1967  NodeProperties::IsExceptionalCall(node, &iterator_exception_node);
1968  int exception_node_index = 0;
1969  if (has_exception_node) {
1970  DCHECK_NOT_NULL(iterator_exception_node);
1971  // If there exists an IfException node for the iterator node, we need
1972  // to merge all the desugared nodes exception. The iterator node will be
1973  // desugared to LoadNamed, Call, CallRuntime, we can pre-allocate the
1974  // nodes with 4 inputs here and we use dead_node as a placeholder for the
1975  // input, which will be replaced.
1976  // We use dead_node as a placeholder for the original exception node before
1977  // it's uses are rewired.
1978 
1979  Node* dead_node = jsgraph()->Dead();
1980  if_exception_merge =
1981  graph()->NewNode(common()->Merge(5), dead_node, dead_node, dead_node,
1982  dead_node, dead_node);
1983  if_exception_effect_phi =
1984  graph()->NewNode(common()->EffectPhi(5), dead_node, dead_node,
1985  dead_node, dead_node, dead_node, if_exception_merge);
1986  if_exception_phi = graph()->NewNode(
1987  common()->Phi(MachineRepresentation::kTagged, 5), dead_node, dead_node,
1988  dead_node, dead_node, dead_node, if_exception_merge);
1989  // Rewire the original exception node uses.
1990  ReplaceWithValue(iterator_exception_node, if_exception_phi,
1991  if_exception_effect_phi, if_exception_merge);
1992  if_exception_merge->ReplaceInput(exception_node_index,
1993  iterator_exception_node);
1994  if_exception_effect_phi->ReplaceInput(exception_node_index,
1995  iterator_exception_node);
1996  if_exception_phi->ReplaceInput(exception_node_index,
1997  iterator_exception_node);
1998  exception_node_index++;
1999  }
2000 
2001  // Load iterator property operator
2002  NameRef iterator_symbol = broker()->iterator_symbol();
2003  const Operator* load_op =
2004  javascript()->LoadNamed(iterator_symbol, p.loadFeedback());
2005 
2006  // Lazy deopt of the load iterator property
2007  // TODO(v8:10047): Use TaggedIndexConstant here once deoptimizer supports it.
2008  Node* call_slot = jsgraph()->SmiConstant(p.callFeedback().slot.ToInt());
2009  Node* call_feedback = jsgraph()->HeapConstantNoHole(p.callFeedback().vector);
2010  Node* lazy_deopt_parameters[] = {receiver, call_slot, call_feedback};
2011  Node* lazy_deopt_frame_state = CreateStubBuiltinContinuationFrameState(
2012  jsgraph(), Builtin::kGetIteratorWithFeedbackLazyDeoptContinuation,
2013  context, lazy_deopt_parameters, arraysize(lazy_deopt_parameters),
2014  frame_state, ContinuationFrameStateMode::LAZY);
2015  Node* load_property =
2016  graph()->NewNode(load_op, receiver, n.feedback_vector(), context,
2017  lazy_deopt_frame_state, effect, control);
2018  effect = load_property;
2019  control = load_property;
2020 
2021  // Merge the exception path for LoadNamed.
2022  if (has_exception_node) {
2023  Node* if_exception =
2024  graph()->NewNode(common()->IfException(), effect, control);
2025  if_exception_merge->ReplaceInput(exception_node_index, if_exception);
2026  if_exception_phi->ReplaceInput(exception_node_index, if_exception);
2027  if_exception_effect_phi->ReplaceInput(exception_node_index, if_exception);
2028  exception_node_index++;
2029  control = graph()->NewNode(common()->IfSuccess(), control);
2030  }
2031 
2032  Node* check = graph()->NewNode(simplified()->ReferenceEqual(), load_property,
2033  jsgraph()->UndefinedConstant());
2034  Node* branch =
2035  graph()->NewNode(common()->Branch(BranchHint::kFalse), check, control);
2036 
2037  {
2038  Node* if_not_iterator = graph()->NewNode(common()->IfTrue(), branch);
2039  Node* effect_not_iterator = effect;
2040  Node* control_not_iterator = if_not_iterator;
2041  Node* call_runtime = effect_not_iterator = control_not_iterator =
2042  graph()->NewNode(
2043  javascript()->CallRuntime(Runtime::kThrowIteratorError, 1),
2044  receiver, context, frame_state, effect_not_iterator,
2045  control_not_iterator);
2046  // Merge the exception path for CallRuntime.
2047  if (has_exception_node) {
2048  Node* if_exception = graph()->NewNode(
2049  common()->IfException(), effect_not_iterator, control_not_iterator);
2050  if_exception_merge->ReplaceInput(exception_node_index, if_exception);
2051  if_exception_phi->ReplaceInput(exception_node_index, if_exception);
2052  if_exception_effect_phi->ReplaceInput(exception_node_index, if_exception);
2053  exception_node_index++;
2054  control_not_iterator =
2055  graph()->NewNode(common()->IfSuccess(), control_not_iterator);
2056  }
2057  Node* throw_node =
2058  graph()->NewNode(common()->Throw(), call_runtime, control_not_iterator);
2059  MergeControlToEnd(graph(), common(), throw_node);
2060  }
2061 
2062  control = graph()->NewNode(common()->IfFalse(), branch);
2063 
2064  // Eager deopt of call iterator property
2065  Node* parameters[] = {receiver, load_property, call_slot, call_feedback};
2066  Node* eager_deopt_frame_state = CreateStubBuiltinContinuationFrameState(
2067  jsgraph(), Builtin::kCallIteratorWithFeedback, context, parameters,
2068  arraysize(parameters), frame_state, ContinuationFrameStateMode::EAGER);
2069  Node* deopt_checkpoint = graph()->NewNode(
2070  common()->Checkpoint(), eager_deopt_frame_state, effect, control);
2071  effect = deopt_checkpoint;
2072 
2073  // Call iterator property operator
2074  ProcessedFeedback const& feedback =
2075  broker()->GetFeedbackForCall(p.callFeedback());
2076  SpeculationMode mode = feedback.IsInsufficient()
2077  ? SpeculationMode::kDisallowSpeculation
2078  : feedback.AsCall().speculation_mode();
2079  const Operator* call_op = javascript()->Call(
2080  JSCallNode::ArityForArgc(0), CallFrequency(), p.callFeedback(),
2081  ConvertReceiverMode::kNotNullOrUndefined, mode,
2082  CallFeedbackRelation::kTarget);
2083  // Lazy deopt to check the call result is JSReceiver.
2084  Node* call_lazy_deopt_frame_state = CreateStubBuiltinContinuationFrameState(
2085  jsgraph(), Builtin::kCallIteratorWithFeedbackLazyDeoptContinuation,
2086  context, nullptr, 0, frame_state, ContinuationFrameStateMode::LAZY);
2087  Node* call_property = effect = control =
2088  graph()->NewNode(call_op, load_property, receiver, n.feedback_vector(),
2089  context, call_lazy_deopt_frame_state, effect, control);
2090 
2091  // Merge the exception path for Call.
2092  if (has_exception_node) {
2093  Node* if_exception =
2094  graph()->NewNode(common()->IfException(), effect, control);
2095  if_exception_merge->ReplaceInput(exception_node_index, if_exception);
2096  if_exception_phi->ReplaceInput(exception_node_index, if_exception);
2097  if_exception_effect_phi->ReplaceInput(exception_node_index, if_exception);
2098  exception_node_index++;
2099  control = graph()->NewNode(common()->IfSuccess(), control);
2100  }
2101 
2102  // If the result is not JSReceiver, throw invalid iterator exception.
2103  Node* is_receiver =
2104  graph()->NewNode(simplified()->ObjectIsReceiver(), call_property);
2105  Node* branch_node = graph()->NewNode(common()->Branch(BranchHint::kTrue),
2106  is_receiver, control);
2107  {
2108  Node* if_not_receiver = graph()->NewNode(common()->IfFalse(), branch_node);
2109  Node* effect_not_receiver = effect;
2110  Node* control_not_receiver = if_not_receiver;
2111  Node* call_runtime = effect_not_receiver = control_not_receiver =
2112  graph()->NewNode(
2113  javascript()->CallRuntime(Runtime::kThrowSymbolIteratorInvalid, 0),
2114  context, frame_state, effect_not_receiver, control_not_receiver);
2115  // Merge the exception path for CallRuntime.
2116  if (has_exception_node) {
2117  Node* if_exception = graph()->NewNode(
2118  common()->IfException(), effect_not_receiver, control_not_receiver);
2119  if_exception_merge->ReplaceInput(exception_node_index, if_exception);
2120  if_exception_phi->ReplaceInput(exception_node_index, if_exception);
2121  if_exception_effect_phi->ReplaceInput(exception_node_index, if_exception);
2122  exception_node_index++;
2123  control_not_receiver =
2124  graph()->NewNode(common()->IfSuccess(), control_not_receiver);
2125  }
2126  Node* throw_node =
2127  graph()->NewNode(common()->Throw(), call_runtime, control_not_receiver);
2128  MergeControlToEnd(graph(), common(), throw_node);
2129  }
2130  Node* if_receiver = graph()->NewNode(common()->IfTrue(), branch_node);
2131  ReplaceWithValue(node, call_property, effect, if_receiver);
2132 
2133  if (has_exception_node) {
2134  DCHECK_EQ(exception_node_index, if_exception_merge->InputCount());
2135  DCHECK_EQ(exception_node_index, if_exception_effect_phi->InputCount() - 1);
2136  DCHECK_EQ(exception_node_index, if_exception_phi->InputCount() - 1);
2137 #ifdef DEBUG
2138  for (Node* input : if_exception_merge->inputs()) {
2139  DCHECK(!input->IsDead());
2140  }
2141  for (Node* input : if_exception_effect_phi->inputs()) {
2142  DCHECK(!input->IsDead());
2143  }
2144  for (Node* input : if_exception_phi->inputs()) {
2145  DCHECK(!input->IsDead());
2146  }
2147 #endif
2148  }
2149  return Replace(if_receiver);
2150 }

2213 void JSNativeContextSpecialization::RemoveImpossibleMaps(
2214  Node* object, ZoneVector<MapRef>* maps) const {
2215  OptionalMapRef root_map = InferRootMap(object);
2216  if (root_map.has_value() && !root_map->is_abandoned_prototype_map()) {
2217  maps->erase(
2218  std::remove_if(maps->begin(), maps->end(),
2219  [root_map, this](MapRef map) {
2220  return map.is_abandoned_prototype_map() ||
2221  !map.FindRootMap(broker()).equals(*root_map);
2222  }),
2223  maps->end());
2224  }
2225 }

2227 // Possibly refine the feedback using inferred map information from the graph.
2228 ElementAccessFeedback const&
2229 JSNativeContextSpecialization::TryRefineElementAccessFeedback(
2230  ElementAccessFeedback const& feedback, Node* receiver,
2231  Effect effect) const {
2232  AccessMode access_mode = feedback.keyed_mode().access_mode();
2233  bool use_inference =
2234  access_mode == AccessMode::kLoad || access_mode == AccessMode::kHas;
2235  if (!use_inference) return feedback;
2236 
2237  ZoneVector<MapRef> inferred_maps(zone());
2238  if (!InferMaps(receiver, effect, &inferred_maps)) return feedback;
2239 
2240  RemoveImpossibleMaps(receiver, &inferred_maps);
2241  // TODO(neis): After Refine, the resulting feedback can still contain
2242  // impossible maps when a target is kept only because more than one of its

2248 Reduction JSNativeContextSpecialization::ReduceElementAccess(
2249  Node* node, Node* index, Node* value,
2250  ElementAccessFeedback const& feedback) {
2251  DCHECK(node->opcode() == IrOpcode::kJSLoadProperty ||
2252  node->opcode() == IrOpcode::kJSSetKeyedProperty ||
2253  node->opcode() == IrOpcode::kJSStoreInArrayLiteral ||
2254  node->opcode() == IrOpcode::kJSDefineKeyedOwnPropertyInLiteral ||
2255  node->opcode() == IrOpcode::kJSHasProperty ||
2256  node->opcode() == IrOpcode::kJSDefineKeyedOwnProperty);
2257  static_assert(JSLoadPropertyNode::ObjectIndex() == 0 &&
2258  JSSetKeyedPropertyNode::ObjectIndex() == 0 &&
2259  JSStoreInArrayLiteralNode::ArrayIndex() == 0 &&
2260  JSDefineKeyedOwnPropertyInLiteralNode::ObjectIndex() == 0 &&
2261  JSHasPropertyNode::ObjectIndex() == 0);
2262 
2263  Node* receiver = NodeProperties::GetValueInput(node, 0);
2264  Effect effect{NodeProperties::GetEffectInput(node)};
2265  Control control{NodeProperties::GetControlInput(node)};
2266  Node* context = NodeProperties::GetContextInput(node);
2267  FrameState frame_state{NodeProperties::GetFrameStateInput(node)};
2268 
2269  // TODO(neis): It's odd that we do optimizations below that don't really care
2270  // about the feedback, but we don't do them when the feedback is megamorphic.
2271  if (feedback.transition_groups().empty()) return NoChange();
2272 
2273  ElementAccessFeedback const& refined_feedback =
2274  TryRefineElementAccessFeedback(feedback, receiver, effect);
2275  LanguageMode language_mode = LanguageMode::kSloppy;
2276  // Only stores (via Proxy) care about strict mode.
2277  if (node->opcode() == IrOpcode::kJSSetKeyedProperty) {
2278  language_mode = JSSetKeyedPropertyNode(node).Parameters().language_mode();
2279  }
2280 
2281  AccessMode access_mode = refined_feedback.keyed_mode().access_mode();
2282  if ((access_mode == AccessMode::kLoad || access_mode == AccessMode::kHas) &&
2283  receiver->opcode() == IrOpcode::kHeapConstant) {
2284  Reduction reduction = ReduceElementLoadFromHeapConstant(
2285  node, index, access_mode, refined_feedback.keyed_mode().load_mode());
2286  if (reduction.Changed()) return reduction;
2287  }
2288 
2289  if (!refined_feedback.transition_groups().empty() &&
2290  refined_feedback.HasOnlyStringMaps(broker())) {
2291  return ReduceElementAccessOnString(node, index, value,
2292  refined_feedback.keyed_mode());
2293  }
2294 
2295  AccessInfoFactory access_info_factory(broker(), graph()->zone());
2296  ZoneVector<ElementAccessInfo> access_infos(zone());
2297  if (!access_info_factory.ComputeElementAccessInfos(refined_feedback,
2298  &access_infos) ||
2299  access_infos.empty()) {
2300  return NoChange();
2301  }
2302 
2303  // Do not optimize AccessMode::kDefine for typed arrays.
2304  if (access_mode == AccessMode::kDefine) {
2305  for (const ElementAccessInfo& access_info : access_infos) {
2306  if (IsTypedArrayOrRabGsabTypedArrayElementsKind(
2307  access_info.elements_kind())) {
2308  return NoChange();
2309  }
2310  }
2311  }
2312 
2313  // For holey stores or growing stores, we need to check that the prototype
2314  // chain contains no setters for elements, and we need to guard those checks
2315  // via code dependencies on the relevant prototype maps.
2316  if (access_mode == AccessMode::kStore) {
2317  // TODO(turbofan): We could have a fast path here, that checks for the
2318  // common case of Array or Object prototype only and therefore avoids
2319  // the zone allocation of this vector.
2320  ZoneVector<MapRef> prototype_maps(zone());
2321  for (ElementAccessInfo const& access_info : access_infos) {
2322  for (MapRef receiver_map : access_info.lookup_start_object_maps()) {
2323  // If the {receiver_map} has a prototype and its elements backing
2324  // store is either holey, or we have a potentially growing store,
2325  // then we need to check that all prototypes have stable maps with
2326  // no element accessors and no throwing behavior for elements (and we
2327  // need to guard against changes to that below).
2328  if ((IsHoleyOrDictionaryElementsKind(receiver_map.elements_kind()) ||
2329  StoreModeCanGrow(feedback.keyed_mode().store_mode())) &&
2330 #if V8_ENABLE_WEBASSEMBLY
2331  !(receiver_map.IsWasmObjectMap() &&
2332  access_info.is_proxy_on_prototype()) &&
2333 #endif // V8_ENABLE_WEBASSEMBLY
2334  !receiver_map.PrototypesElementsDoNotHaveAccessorsOrThrow(
2335  broker(), &prototype_maps)) {
2336  return NoChange();
2337  }
2338 
2339  // TODO(v8:12547): Support writing to objects in shared space, which
2340  // need a write barrier that calls Object::Share to ensure the RHS is
2341  // shared.
2342  if (InstanceTypeChecker::IsAlwaysSharedSpaceJSObject(
2343  receiver_map.instance_type())) {
2344  return NoChange();
2345  }
2346  }
2347  }
2348  for (MapRef prototype_map : prototype_maps) {
2349  dependencies()->DependOnStableMap(prototype_map);
2350  }
2351  } else if (access_mode == AccessMode::kHas) {
2352  // If we have any fast arrays, we need to check and depend on
2353  // NoElementsProtector.
2354  for (ElementAccessInfo const& access_info : access_infos) {
2355  if (IsFastElementsKind(access_info.elements_kind())) {
2356  if (!dependencies()->DependOnNoElementsProtector()) return NoChange();
2357  break;
2358  }
2359  }
2360  }
2361 
2362  // Collect call nodes to rewire exception edges.
2363  ZoneVector<Node*> if_exception_nodes(zone());
2364  ZoneVector<Node*>* if_exceptions = nullptr;
2365  Node* if_exception = nullptr;
2366  if (NodeProperties::IsExceptionalCall(node, &if_exception)) {
2367  if_exceptions = &if_exception_nodes;
2368  }
2369 
2370  // Check for the monomorphic case.
2371  PropertyAccessBuilder access_builder(jsgraph(), broker());
2372  if (access_infos.size() == 1) {
2373  const ElementAccessInfo& access_info = access_infos.front();
2374 
2375  if (!access_info.transition_sources().empty()) {
2376  DCHECK_EQ(access_info.lookup_start_object_maps().size(), 1);
2377  // Perform possible elements kind transitions.
2378  MapRef transition_target = access_info.lookup_start_object_maps().front();
2379  ZoneRefSet<Map> sources(access_info.transition_sources().begin(),
2380  access_info.transition_sources().end(),
2381  graph()->zone());
2382  effect = graph()->NewNode(simplified()->TransitionElementsKindOrCheckMap(
2383  ElementsTransitionWithMultipleSources(
2384  sources, transition_target)),
2385  receiver, effect, control);
2386  } else {
2387  // Perform map check on the {receiver}.
2388  access_builder.BuildCheckMaps(receiver, &effect, control,
2389  access_info.lookup_start_object_maps());
2390  }
2391 
2392  // Access the actual element.
2393  ValueEffectControl continuation = BuildElementAccess(
2394  receiver, index, value, effect, control, context, access_info,
2395  language_mode, feedback.keyed_mode(), if_exceptions, frame_state);
2396  value = continuation.value();
2397  effect = continuation.effect();
2398  control = continuation.control();
2399  } else {
2400  // The final states for every polymorphic branch. We join them with
2401  // Merge+Phi+EffectPhi at the bottom.
2402  ZoneVector<Node*> values(zone());
2403  ZoneVector<Node*> effects(zone());
2404  ZoneVector<Node*> controls(zone());
2405 
2406  // Generate code for the various different element access patterns.
2407  Node* fallthrough_control = control;
2408  for (size_t j = 0; j < access_infos.size(); ++j) {
2409  ElementAccessInfo const& access_info = access_infos[j];
2410  Node* this_receiver = receiver;
2411  Node* this_value = value;
2412  Node* this_index = index;
2413  Effect this_effect = effect;
2414  Control this_control{fallthrough_control};
2415 
2416  // Perform possible elements kind transitions.
2417  MapRef transition_target = access_info.lookup_start_object_maps().front();
2418  for (MapRef transition_source : access_info.transition_sources()) {
2419  DCHECK_EQ(access_info.lookup_start_object_maps().size(), 1);
2420  this_effect = graph()->NewNode(
2421  simplified()->TransitionElementsKind(ElementsTransition(
2422  IsSimpleMapChangeTransition(transition_source.elements_kind(),
2423  transition_target.elements_kind())
2424  ? ElementsTransition::kFastTransition
2425  : ElementsTransition::kSlowTransition,
2426  transition_source, transition_target)),
2427  receiver, this_effect, this_control);
2428  }
2429 
2430  // Perform map check(s) on {receiver}.
2431  ZoneVector<MapRef> const& receiver_maps =
2432  access_info.lookup_start_object_maps();
2433  if (j == access_infos.size() - 1) {
2434  // Last map check on the fallthrough control path, do a
2435  // conditional eager deoptimization exit here.
2436  access_builder.BuildCheckMaps(receiver, &this_effect, this_control,
2437  receiver_maps);
2438  fallthrough_control = nullptr;
2439  } else {
2440  // Explicitly branch on the {receiver_maps}.
2441  ZoneRefSet<Map> maps(receiver_maps.begin(), receiver_maps.end(),
2442  graph()->zone());
2443  Node* check = this_effect =
2444  graph()->NewNode(simplified()->CompareMaps(maps), receiver,
2445  this_effect, fallthrough_control);
2446  Node* branch =
2447  graph()->NewNode(common()->Branch(), check, fallthrough_control);
2448  fallthrough_control = graph()->NewNode(common()->IfFalse(), branch);
2449  this_control = graph()->NewNode(common()->IfTrue(), branch);
2450 
2451  // Introduce a MapGuard to learn from this on the effect chain.
2452  this_effect = graph()->NewNode(simplified()->MapGuard(maps), receiver,
2453  this_effect, this_control);
2454  }
2455 
2456  // Access the actual element.
2457  ValueEffectControl continuation =
2458  BuildElementAccess(this_receiver, this_index, this_value, this_effect,
2459  this_control, context, access_info, language_mode,
2460  feedback.keyed_mode(), if_exceptions, frame_state);
2461  values.push_back(continuation.value());
2462  effects.push_back(continuation.effect());
2463  controls.push_back(continuation.control());
2464  }
2465 
2466  DCHECK_NULL(fallthrough_control);
2467 
2468  // Generate the final merge point for all (polymorphic) branches.
2469  int const control_count = static_cast<int>(controls.size());
2470  if (control_count == 0) {
2471  value = effect = control = jsgraph()->Dead();
2472  } else if (control_count == 1) {
2473  value = values.front();
2474  effect = effects.front();
2475  control = controls.front();
2476  } else {
2477  control = graph()->NewNode(common()->Merge(control_count), control_count,
2478  &controls.front());
2479  values.push_back(control);
2480  value = graph()->NewNode(
2481  common()->Phi(MachineRepresentation::kTagged, control_count),
2482  control_count + 1, &values.front());
2483  effects.push_back(control);
2484  effect = graph()->NewNode(common()->EffectPhi(control_count),
2485  control_count + 1, &effects.front());
2486  }
2487  }
2488 
2489  // Properly rewire IfException edges if {node} is inside a try-block.
2490  if (!if_exception_nodes.empty()) {
2491  DCHECK_NOT_NULL(if_exception);
2492  DCHECK_EQ(if_exceptions, &if_exception_nodes);
2493  int const if_exception_count = static_cast<int>(if_exceptions->size());
2494  Node* merge = graph()->NewNode(common()->Merge(if_exception_count),
2495  if_exception_count, &if_exceptions->front());
2496  if_exceptions->push_back(merge);
2497  Node* ephi =
2498  graph()->NewNode(common()->EffectPhi(if_exception_count),
2499  if_exception_count + 1, &if_exceptions->front());
2500  Node* phi = graph()->NewNode(
2501  common()->Phi(MachineRepresentation::kTagged, if_exception_count),
2502  if_exception_count + 1, &if_exceptions->front());
2503  ReplaceWithValue(if_exception, phi, ephi, merge);
2504  }
2505 
2506  ReplaceWithValue(node, value, effect, control);
2507  return Replace(value);
2508 }

2510 Reduction JSNativeContextSpecialization::ReduceElementLoadFromHeapConstant(
2511  Node* node, Node* key, AccessMode access_mode,
2512  KeyedAccessLoadMode load_mode) {
2513  DCHECK(node->opcode() == IrOpcode::kJSLoadProperty ||
2514  node->opcode() == IrOpcode::kJSHasProperty);
2515  Node* receiver = NodeProperties::GetValueInput(node, 0);
2516  Node* effect = NodeProperties::GetEffectInput(node);
2517  Node* control = NodeProperties::GetControlInput(node);
2518 
2519  HeapObjectMatcher mreceiver(receiver);
2520  HeapObjectRef receiver_ref = mreceiver.Ref(broker());
2521  if (receiver_ref.IsNull() || receiver_ref.IsUndefined() ||
2522  // The 'in' operator throws a TypeError on primitive values.
2523  (receiver_ref.IsString() && access_mode == AccessMode::kHas)) {
2524  return NoChange();
2525  }
2526 
2527  // Check whether we're accessing a known element on the {receiver} and can
2528  // constant-fold the load.
2529  NumberMatcher mkey(key);
2530  if (mkey.IsInteger() &&
2531  mkey.IsInRange(0.0, static_cast<double>(JSObject::kMaxElementIndex))) {
2532  static_assert(JSObject::kMaxElementIndex <= kMaxUInt32);
2533  const uint32_t index = static_cast<uint32_t>(mkey.ResolvedValue());
2534  OptionalObjectRef element;
2535 
2536  if (receiver_ref.IsJSObject()) {
2537  JSObjectRef jsobject_ref = receiver_ref.AsJSObject();
2538  OptionalFixedArrayBaseRef elements =
2539  jsobject_ref.elements(broker(), kRelaxedLoad);
2540  if (elements.has_value()) {
2541  element = jsobject_ref.GetOwnConstantElement(broker(), *elements, index,
2542  dependencies());
2543  if (!element.has_value() && receiver_ref.IsJSArray()) {
2544  // We didn't find a constant element, but if the receiver is a
2545  // cow-array we can exploit the fact that any future write to the
2546  // element will replace the whole elements storage.
2547  element = receiver_ref.AsJSArray().GetOwnCowElement(broker(),
2548  *elements, index);
2549  if (element.has_value()) {
2550  Node* actual_elements = effect = graph()->NewNode(
2551  simplified()->LoadField(AccessBuilder::ForJSObjectElements()),
2552  receiver, effect, control);
2553  Node* check = graph()->NewNode(
2554  simplified()->ReferenceEqual(), actual_elements,
2555  jsgraph()->ConstantNoHole(*elements, broker()));
2556  effect = graph()->NewNode(
2557  simplified()->CheckIf(
2558  DeoptimizeReason::kCowArrayElementsChanged),
2559  check, effect, control);
2560  }
2561  }
2562  }
2563  } else if (receiver_ref.IsString()) {
2564  element =
2565  receiver_ref.AsString().GetCharAsStringOrUndefined(broker(), index);
2566  }
2567 
2568  if (element.has_value()) {
2569  Node* value = access_mode == AccessMode::kHas
2570  ? jsgraph()->TrueConstant()
2571  : jsgraph()->ConstantNoHole(*element, broker());
2572  ReplaceWithValue(node, value, effect, control);
2573  return Replace(value);
2574  }
2575  }
2576 
2577  // For constant Strings we can eagerly strength-reduce the keyed
2578  // accesses using the known length, which doesn't change.
2579  if (receiver_ref.IsString()) {
2580  DCHECK_NE(access_mode, AccessMode::kHas);
2581  // Ensure that {key} is less than {receiver} length.
2582  Node* length = jsgraph()->ConstantNoHole(receiver_ref.AsString().length());
2583 
2584  // Load the single character string from {receiver} or yield
2585  // undefined if the {key} is out of bounds (depending on the
2586  // {load_mode}).
2587  Node* value = BuildIndexedStringLoad(receiver, key, length, &effect,
2588  &control, load_mode);
2589  ReplaceWithValue(node, value, effect, control);
2590  return Replace(value);
2591  }
2592 
2593  return NoChange();
2594 }

2596 Reduction JSNativeContextSpecialization::ReducePropertyAccess(
2597  Node* node, Node* key, OptionalNameRef static_name, Node* value,
2598  FeedbackSource const& source, AccessMode access_mode) {
2599  DCHECK_EQ(key == nullptr, static_name.has_value());
2600  DCHECK(node->opcode() == IrOpcode::kJSLoadProperty ||
2601  node->opcode() == IrOpcode::kJSSetKeyedProperty ||
2602  node->opcode() == IrOpcode::kJSStoreInArrayLiteral ||
2603  node->opcode() == IrOpcode::kJSDefineKeyedOwnPropertyInLiteral ||
2604  node->opcode() == IrOpcode::kJSHasProperty ||
2605  node->opcode() == IrOpcode::kJSLoadNamed ||
2606  node->opcode() == IrOpcode::kJSSetNamedProperty ||
2607  node->opcode() == IrOpcode::kJSDefineNamedOwnProperty ||
2608  node->opcode() == IrOpcode::kJSLoadNamedFromSuper ||
2609  node->opcode() == IrOpcode::kJSDefineKeyedOwnProperty);
2610  DCHECK_GE(node->op()->ControlOutputCount(), 1);
2611 
2612  ProcessedFeedback const* feedback =
2613  &broker()->GetFeedbackForPropertyAccess(source, access_mode, static_name);
2614 
2615  if (feedback->kind() == ProcessedFeedback::kElementAccess &&
2616  feedback->AsElementAccess().transition_groups().empty()) {
2617  HeapObjectMatcher m_key(key);
2618  if (m_key.HasResolvedValue() && m_key.Ref(broker()).IsName()) {
2619  NameRef name_key = m_key.Ref(broker()).AsName();
2620  if (name_key.IsUniqueName() && !name_key.object()->IsArrayIndex()) {
2621  feedback = &feedback->AsElementAccess().Refine(
2622  broker(), m_key.Ref(broker()).AsName());
2623  }
2624  }
2625  }
2626 
2627  switch (feedback->kind()) {
2628  case ProcessedFeedback::kInsufficient:
2629  return ReduceEagerDeoptimize(
2630  node,
2631  DeoptimizeReason::kInsufficientTypeFeedbackForGenericNamedAccess);
2632  case ProcessedFeedback::kNamedAccess:
2633  return ReduceNamedAccess(node, value, feedback->AsNamedAccess(),
2634  access_mode, key);
2635  case ProcessedFeedback::kMegaDOMPropertyAccess:
2636  DCHECK_EQ(access_mode, AccessMode::kLoad);
2637  DCHECK_NULL(key);
2638  return ReduceMegaDOMPropertyAccess(
2639  node, value, feedback->AsMegaDOMPropertyAccess(), source);
2640  case ProcessedFeedback::kElementAccess:
2641  DCHECK_EQ(feedback->AsElementAccess().keyed_mode().access_mode(),
2642  access_mode);
2643  DCHECK_NE(node->opcode(), IrOpcode::kJSLoadNamedFromSuper);
2644  return ReduceElementAccess(node, key, value, feedback->AsElementAccess());
2645  default:
2646  UNREACHABLE();
2647  }
2648 }

2650 Reduction JSNativeContextSpecialization::ReduceEagerDeoptimize(
2651  Node* node, DeoptimizeReason reason) {
2652  if (!(flags() & kBailoutOnUninitialized)) return NoChange();
2653 
2654  Node* effect = NodeProperties::GetEffectInput(node);
2655  Node* control = NodeProperties::GetControlInput(node);
2656  Node* frame_state =

2659  graph()->NewNode(common()->Deoptimize(reason, FeedbackSource()),
2660  frame_state, effect, control);
2661  MergeControlToEnd(graph(), common(), deoptimize);
2662  node->TrimInputCount(0);
2663  NodeProperties::ChangeOp(node, common()->Dead());

2675 
2676 Reduction JSNativeContextSpecialization::ReduceJSLoadPropertyWithEnumeratedKey(
2677  Node* node) {
2678  // We can optimize a property load if it's being used inside a for..in:
2679  // for (name in receiver) {
2680  // value = receiver[name];
2681  // ...
2682  // }
2683  //
2684  // If the for..in is in fast-mode, we know that the {receiver} has {name}
2685  // as own property, otherwise the enumeration wouldn't include it. The graph
2686  // constructed by the BytecodeGraphBuilder in this case looks like this:
2687 
2688  // receiver
2689  // ^ ^
2690  // | |
2691  // | +-+
2692  // | |
2693  // | JSToObject
2694  // | ^
2695  // | |
2696  // | |
2697  // | JSForInNext
2698  // | ^
2699  // | |
2700  // +----+ |
2701  // | |
2702  // | |
2703  // JSLoadProperty
2704 
2705  // If the for..in has only seen maps with enum cache consisting of keys
2706  // and indices so far, we can turn the {JSLoadProperty} into a map check
2707  // on the {receiver} and then just load the field value dynamically via
2708  // the {LoadFieldByIndex} operator. The map check is only necessary when
2709  // TurboFan cannot prove that there is no observable side effect between
2710  // the {JSForInNext} and the {JSLoadProperty} node.
2711  //
2712  // We can do a similar optimization when the receiver of {JSLoadProperty} is
2713  // not identical to the receiver of {JSForInNext}:
2714  // for (name in receiver) {
2715  // value = object[name];
2716  // ...
2717  // }
2718  //
2719  // This is because when the key is {JSForInNext}, we will generate a
2720  // {GetEnumeratedKeyedProperty} bytecode for {JSLoadProperty}. If the bytecode
2721  // always manages to use the enum cache, we will keep the inline cache in
2722  // uninitialized state. So If the graph is as below, we can firstly do a map
2723  // check on {object} and then turn the {JSLoadProperty} into the
2724  // {LoadFieldByIndex}. This is also safe when the bytecode has never been
2725  // profiled. When it happens to pass the the map check, we can use the fast
2726  // path. Otherwise it will trigger a deoptimization.
2727 
2728  // object receiver
2729  // ^ ^
2730  // | |
2731  // | |
2732  // | |
2733  // | JSToObject
2734  // | ^
2735  // | |
2736  // | |
2737  // | JSForInNext
2738  // | ^
2739  // | |
2740  // +----+ +-----+
2741  // | |
2742  // | |
2743  // JSLoadProperty (insufficient feedback)
2744 
2745  // Also note that it's safe to look through the {JSToObject}, since the
2746  // [[Get]] operation does an implicit ToObject anyway, and these operations
2747  // are not observable.
2748 
2749  DCHECK_EQ(IrOpcode::kJSLoadProperty, node->opcode());
2750  Node* receiver = NodeProperties::GetValueInput(node, 0);
2751  JSForInNextNode name(NodeProperties::GetValueInput(node, 1));
2752  Node* effect = NodeProperties::GetEffectInput(node);
2753  Node* control = NodeProperties::GetControlInput(node);
2754 
2755  if (name.Parameters().mode() != ForInMode::kUseEnumCacheKeysAndIndices) {
2756  return NoChange();
2757  }
2758 
2759  Node* object = name.receiver();
2760  Node* cache_type = name.cache_type();
2761  Node* index = name.index();
2762  if (object->opcode() == IrOpcode::kJSToObject) {
2763  object = NodeProperties::GetValueInput(object, 0);
2764  }
2765  bool speculating_object_is_receiver = false;
2766  if (object != receiver) {
2767  JSLoadPropertyNode n(node);
2768  PropertyAccess const& p = n.Parameters();
2769 
2770  ProcessedFeedback const& feedback = broker()->GetFeedbackForPropertyAccess(
2771  FeedbackSource(p.feedback()), AccessMode::kLoad, std::nullopt);
2772  // When the feedback is uninitialized, it is either a load from a
2773  // {GetEnumeratedKeyedProperty} which always hits the enum cache, or a keyed
2774  // load that had never been reached. In either case, we can check the map
2775  // of the receiver and use the enum cache if the map match the {cache_type}.
2776  if (feedback.kind() != ProcessedFeedback::kInsufficient) {
2777  return NoChange();
2778  }
2779 
2780  // Ensure that {receiver} is a HeapObject.
2781  receiver = effect = graph()->NewNode(simplified()->CheckHeapObject(),
2782  receiver, effect, control);
2783  speculating_object_is_receiver = true;
2784  }
2785 
2786  // No need to repeat the map check if we can prove that there's no
2787  // observable side effect between {effect} and {name]. But we always need a
2788  // map check when {object} is not identical to {receiver}.
2789  if (!NodeProperties::NoObservableSideEffectBetween(effect, name) ||
2790  speculating_object_is_receiver) {
2791  // Check that the {receiver} map is still valid.
2792  Node* receiver_map = effect =
2793  graph()->NewNode(simplified()->LoadField(AccessBuilder::ForMap()),
2794  receiver, effect, control);
2795  Node* check = graph()->NewNode(simplified()->ReferenceEqual(), receiver_map,
2796  cache_type);
2797  effect =
2798  graph()->NewNode(simplified()->CheckIf(DeoptimizeReason::kWrongMap),
2799  check, effect, control);
2800  }
2801 
2802  // Load the enum cache indices from the {cache_type}.
2803  Node* descriptor_array = effect = graph()->NewNode(
2804  simplified()->LoadField(AccessBuilder::ForMapDescriptors()), cache_type,
2805  effect, control);
2806  Node* enum_cache = effect = graph()->NewNode(
2807  simplified()->LoadField(AccessBuilder::ForDescriptorArrayEnumCache()),
2808  descriptor_array, effect, control);
2809  Node* enum_indices = effect = graph()->NewNode(
2810  simplified()->LoadField(AccessBuilder::ForEnumCacheIndices()), enum_cache,
2811  effect, control);
2812 
2813  // Ensure that the {enum_indices} are valid.
2814  Node* check = graph()->NewNode(
2815  simplified()->BooleanNot(),
2816  graph()->NewNode(simplified()->ReferenceEqual(), enum_indices,
2817  jsgraph()->EmptyFixedArrayConstant()));
2818  effect = graph()->NewNode(
2819  simplified()->CheckIf(DeoptimizeReason::kWrongEnumIndices), check, effect,
2820  control);
2821 
2822  // Determine the key from the {enum_indices}.
2823  Node* key = effect = graph()->NewNode(
2824  simplified()->LoadElement(
2825  AccessBuilder::ForFixedArrayElement(PACKED_SMI_ELEMENTS)),
2826  enum_indices, index, effect, control);
2827 
2828  // Load the actual field value.
2829  Node* value = effect = graph()->NewNode(simplified()->LoadFieldByIndex(),
2830  receiver, key, effect, control);
2831  ReplaceWithValue(node, value, effect, control);
2832  return Replace(value);
2833 }

3314  DCHECK(field_representation == MachineRepresentation::kTagged);
3315  }
3316  break;
3317  case MachineRepresentation::kNone:
3318  case MachineRepresentation::kBit:
3319  case MachineRepresentation::kCompressedPointer:
3320  case MachineRepresentation::kCompressed:
3321  case MachineRepresentation::kProtectedPointer:
3322  case MachineRepresentation::kIndirectPointer:
3323  case MachineRepresentation::kSandboxedPointer:
3324  case MachineRepresentation::kWord8:
3325  case MachineRepresentation::kWord16:
3326  case MachineRepresentation::kWord32:
3327  case MachineRepresentation::kWord64:
3328  case MachineRepresentation::kFloat16:
3329  case MachineRepresentation::kFloat32:
3330  case MachineRepresentation::kSimd128:
3331  case MachineRepresentation::kSimd256:
3332  case MachineRepresentation::kMapWord:
3333  case MachineRepresentation::kFloat16RawBits:
3334  UNREACHABLE();
3335  }
3336  // Check if we need to perform a transitioning store.
3337  OptionalMapRef transition_map = access_info.transition_map();
3338  if (transition_map.has_value()) {
3339  // Check if we need to grow the properties backing store
3340  // with this transitioning store.
3341  MapRef transition_map_ref = transition_map.value();
3342  MapRef original_map = transition_map_ref.GetBackPointer(broker()).AsMap();
3343  if (!field_index.is_inobject()) {
3344  // If slack tracking ends after this compilation started but before it's
3345  // finished, then we could {original_map} could be out-of-sync with
3346  // {transition_map_ref}. In particular, its UnusedPropertyFields could
3347  // be non-zero, which would lead us to not extend the property backing
3348  // store, while the underlying Map has actually zero
3349  // UnusedPropertyFields. Thus, we install a dependency on {orininal_map}
3350  // now, so that if such a situation happens, we'll throw away the code.
3351  dependencies()->DependOnNoSlackTrackingChange(original_map);
3352  }
3353  if (original_map.UnusedPropertyFields() == 0) {
3354  DCHECK(!field_index.is_inobject());
3355 
3356  // Reallocate the properties {storage}.
3357  storage = effect = BuildExtendPropertiesBackingStore(
3358  original_map, storage, effect, control);
3359 
3360  // Perform the actual store.
3361  effect = graph()->NewNode(simplified()->StoreField(field_access),
3362  storage, value, effect, control);
3363 
3364  // Atomically switch to the new properties below.
3365  field_access = AccessBuilder::ForJSObjectPropertiesOrHashKnownPointer();
3366  value = storage;
3367  storage = receiver;
3368  }
3369  effect = graph()->NewNode(
3370  common()->BeginRegion(RegionObservability::kObservable), effect);
3371  effect = graph()->NewNode(
3372  simplified()->StoreField(AccessBuilder::ForMap()), receiver,
3373  jsgraph()->ConstantNoHole(transition_map_ref, broker()), effect,
3374  control);
3375  effect = graph()->NewNode(simplified()->StoreField(field_access), storage,
3376  value, effect, control);
3377  effect = graph()->NewNode(common()->FinishRegion(),
3378  jsgraph()->UndefinedConstant(), effect);
3379  } else {
3380  // Regular non-transitioning field store.
3381  effect = graph()->NewNode(simplified()->StoreField(field_access), storage,
3382  value, effect, control);
3383  }
3384  }
3385 
3386  return ValueEffectControl(value, effect, control);
3387 }

3522 JSNativeContextSpecialization::ValueEffectControl
3523 JSNativeContextSpecialization::BuildElementAccess(
3524  Node* receiver, Node* index, Node* value, Node* effect, Node* control,
3525  Node* context, ElementAccessInfo const& access_info,
3526  LanguageMode language_mode, KeyedAccessMode const& keyed_mode,
3527  ZoneVector<Node*>* if_exceptions, Node* frame_state) {
3528  // TODO(bmeurer): We currently specialize based on elements kind. We should
3529  // also be able to properly support strings and other JSObjects here.
3530  ElementsKind elements_kind = access_info.elements_kind();
3531  ZoneVector<MapRef> const& receiver_maps =
3532  access_info.lookup_start_object_maps();
3533 
3534  if (IsTypedArrayElementsKind(elements_kind) ||
3535  IsRabGsabTypedArrayElementsKind(elements_kind)) {
3536  return BuildElementAccessForTypedArrayOrRabGsabTypedArray(
3537  receiver, index, value, effect, control, context, elements_kind,

3539  }
3540 
3541 #if V8_ENABLE_WEBASSEMBLY

3543  access_info.is_proxy_on_prototype()) {

3546  language_mode, keyed_mode, if_exceptions, frame_state);
3547  }

3549 
3550  // Load the elements for the {receiver}.
3551  Node* elements = effect = graph()->NewNode(
3552  simplified()->LoadField(AccessBuilder::ForJSObjectElements()), receiver,
3553  effect, control);
3554 
3555  // Don't try to store to a copy-on-write backing store (unless supported by
3556  // the store mode).

3558  IsSmiOrObjectElementsKind(elements_kind) &&
3559  !StoreModeHandlesCOW(keyed_mode.store_mode())) {
3560  effect = graph()->NewNode(
3561  simplified()->CheckMaps(CheckMapsFlag::kNone,
3562  ZoneRefSet<Map>(broker()->fixed_array_map())),
3563  elements, effect, control);

3567  bool receiver_is_jsarray = HasOnlyJSArrayMaps(broker(), receiver_maps);
3568

3570  Node* length = effect =
3571  receiver_is_jsarray
3572  ? graph()->NewNode(
3573  simplified()->LoadField(
3574  AccessBuilder::ForJSArrayLength(elements_kind)),
3575  receiver, effect, control)
3576  : graph()->NewNode(
3577  simplified()->LoadField(AccessBuilder::ForFixedArrayLength()),
3578  elements, effect, control);

3580  // Check if we might need to grow the {elements} backing store.
3581  if (keyed_mode.IsStore() && StoreModeCanGrow(keyed_mode.store_mode())) {
3582  // For growing stores we validate the {index} below.
3583  } else if (keyed_mode.IsLoad() &&
3584  LoadModeHandlesOOB(keyed_mode.load_mode()) &&
3585  CanTreatHoleAsUndefined(receiver_maps)) {

3590  simplified()->CheckBounds(FeedbackSource(),
3591  CheckBoundsFlag::kConvertStringAndMinusZero),
3592  index, jsgraph()->ConstantNoHole(Smi::kMaxValue), effect, control);
3593  } else {
3594  // Check that the {index} is in the valid range for the {receiver}.
3595  index = effect = graph()->NewNode(
3596  simplified()->CheckBounds(FeedbackSource(),
3597  CheckBoundsFlag::kConvertStringAndMinusZero),
3598  index, length, effect, control);
3599  }
3600

3602  Type element_type = Type::NonInternal();
3603  MachineType element_machine_type = MachineType::AnyTagged();
3604  if (IsDoubleElementsKind(elements_kind)) {
3605  element_type = Type::Number();
3606 #ifdef V8_ENABLE_EXPERIMENTAL_UNDEFINED_DOUBLE
3607  if (elements_kind == HOLEY_DOUBLE_ELEMENTS) {
3608  element_type =
3609  Type::Union(element_type, Type::Undefined(), graph()->zone());
3610  }
3611 #endif // V8_ENABLE_EXPERIMENTAL_UNDEFINED_DOUBLE

3613  } else if (IsSmiElementsKind(elements_kind)) {
3614  element_type = Type::SignedSmall();
3615  element_machine_type = MachineType::TaggedSigned();
3616  }
3617  ElementAccess element_access = {kTaggedBase, OFFSET_OF_DATA_START(FixedArray),
3618  element_type, element_machine_type,

3636  CanTreatHoleAsUndefined(receiver_maps)) {

3638  graph()->NewNode(simplified()->NumberLessThan(), index, length);

3640  graph()->NewNode(common()->Branch(BranchHint::kTrue), check, control);
3641

3855  graph()->NewNode(simplified()->EnsureWritableFastElements(), receiver,
3856  elements, effect, control);
3857  } else if (StoreModeCanGrow(keyed_mode.store_mode())) {
3858  // Determine the length of the {elements} backing store.
3859  Node* elements_length = effect = graph()->NewNode(
3860  simplified()->LoadField(AccessBuilder::ForFixedArrayLength()),
3861  elements, effect, control);
3862 
3863  // Validate the {index} depending on holeyness:
3864  //
3865  // For HOLEY_*_ELEMENTS the {index} must not exceed the {elements}
3866  // backing store capacity plus the maximum allowed gap, as otherwise
3867  // the (potential) backing store growth would normalize and thus
3868  // the elements kind of the {receiver} would change to slow mode.
3869  //
3870  // For JSArray PACKED_*_ELEMENTS the {index} must be within the range
3871  // [0,length+1[ to be valid. In case {index} equals {length},
3872  // the {receiver} will be extended, but kept packed.
3873  //
3874  // Non-JSArray PACKED_*_ELEMENTS always grow by adding holes because they
3875  // lack the magical length property, which requires a map transition.
3876  // So we can assume that this did not happen if we did not see this map.
3877  Node* limit =
3878  IsHoleyElementsKind(elements_kind)
3879  ? graph()->NewNode(simplified()->NumberAdd(), elements_length,
3880  jsgraph()->ConstantNoHole(JSObject::kMaxGap))
3881  : receiver_is_jsarray
3882  ? graph()->NewNode(simplified()->NumberAdd(), length,
3883  jsgraph()->OneConstant())
3884  : elements_length;
3885  index = effect = graph()->NewNode(
3886  simplified()->CheckBounds(
3887  FeedbackSource(), CheckBoundsFlag::kConvertStringAndMinusZero),
3888  index, limit, effect, control);
3889 
3890  // Grow {elements} backing store if necessary.
3891  GrowFastElementsMode mode =
3892  IsDoubleElementsKind(elements_kind)
3893  ? GrowFastElementsMode::kDoubleElements
3894  : GrowFastElementsMode::kSmiOrObjectElements;
3895  elements = effect = graph()->NewNode(
3896  simplified()->MaybeGrowFastElements(mode, FeedbackSource()), receiver,
3897  elements, index, elements_length, effect, control);
3898 
3899  // If we didn't grow {elements}, it might still be COW, in which case we
3900  // copy it now.
3901  if (IsSmiOrObjectElementsKind(elements_kind) &&
3902  keyed_mode.store_mode() == KeyedAccessStoreMode::kGrowAndHandleCOW) {
3903  elements = effect =
3904  graph()->NewNode(simplified()->EnsureWritableFastElements(),
3905  receiver, elements, effect, control);
3906  }
3907 
3908  // Also update the "length" property if {receiver} is a JSArray.
3909  if (receiver_is_jsarray) {
3910  Node* check =
3911  graph()->NewNode(simplified()->NumberLessThan(), index, length);
3912  Node* branch = graph()->NewNode(common()->Branch(), check, control);
3913 
3914  Node* if_true = graph()->NewNode(common()->IfTrue(), branch);
3915  Node* etrue = effect;
3916  {
3917  // We don't need to do anything, the {index} is within
3918  // the valid bounds for the JSArray {receiver}.
3919  }
3920 
3921  Node* if_false = graph()->NewNode(common()->IfFalse(), branch);
3922  Node* efalse = effect;
3923  {
3924  // Update the JSArray::length field. Since this is observable,
3925  // there must be no other check after this.
3926  Node* new_length = graph()->NewNode(simplified()->NumberAdd(), index,
3927  jsgraph()->OneConstant());
3928  efalse = graph()->NewNode(
3929  simplified()->StoreField(
3930  AccessBuilder::ForJSArrayLength(elements_kind)),
3931  receiver, new_length, efalse, if_false);
3932  }
3933 
3934  control = graph()->NewNode(common()->Merge(2), if_true, if_false);
3935  effect =
3936  graph()->NewNode(common()->EffectPhi(2), etrue, efalse, control);
3937  }
3938  }
3939 
3940  // Perform the actual element access.
3941  effect = graph()->NewNode(simplified()->StoreElement(element_access),
3942  elements, index, value, effect, control);
3943  }
3944 
3945  return ValueEffectControl(value, effect, control);
3946 }

4251  }
4252  break;
4253  }
4254

4303  index = *effect = graph()->NewNode(

4309  Node* value = *effect = graph()->NewNode(

4316 Node* JSNativeContextSpecialization::BuildExtendPropertiesBackingStore(
4317  MapRef map, Node* properties, Node* effect, Node* control) {
4318  // TODO(bmeurer/jkummerow): Property deletions can undo map transitions
4319  // while keeping the backing store around, meaning that even though the
4320  // map might believe that objects have no unused property fields, there
4321  // might actually be some. It would be nice to not create a new backing
4322  // store in that case (i.e. when properties->length() >= new_length).
4323  // However, introducing branches and Phi nodes here would make it more
4324  // difficult for escape analysis to get rid of the backing stores used
4325  // for intermediate states of chains of property additions. That makes
4326  // it unclear what the best approach is here.
4327  DCHECK_EQ(map.UnusedPropertyFields(), 0);
4328  int length = map.NextFreePropertyIndex() - map.GetInObjectProperties();
4329  // Under normal circumstances, NextFreePropertyIndex() will always be larger
4330  // than GetInObjectProperties(). However, an attacker able to corrupt heap
4331  // memory can break this invariant, in which case we'll get confused here,
4332  // potentially causing a sandbox violation. This CHECK defends against that.
4333  SBXCHECK_GE(length, 0);
4334  int new_length = length + JSObject::kFieldsAdded;
4335  // Collect the field values from the {properties}.
4336  ZoneVector<Node*> values(zone());
4337  values.reserve(new_length);
4338  for (int i = 0; i < length; ++i) {
4339  Node* value = effect = graph()->NewNode(
4340  simplified()->LoadField(AccessBuilder::ForFixedArraySlot(i)),
4341  properties, effect, control);
4342  values.push_back(value);
4343  }
4344  // Initialize the new fields to undefined.
4345  for (int i = 0; i < JSObject::kFieldsAdded; ++i) {
4346  values.push_back(jsgraph()->UndefinedConstant());
4347  }
4348 
4349  // Compute new length and hash.
4350  Node* hash;
4351  if (length == 0) {
4352  hash = graph()->NewNode(
4353  common()->Select(MachineRepresentation::kTaggedSigned),
4354  graph()->NewNode(simplified()->ObjectIsSmi(), properties), properties,
4355  jsgraph()->SmiConstant(PropertyArray::kNoHashSentinel));
4356  hash = effect = graph()->NewNode(common()->TypeGuard(Type::SignedSmall()),
4357  hash, effect, control);
4358  hash = graph()->NewNode(
4359  simplified()->NumberShiftLeft(), hash,
4360  jsgraph()->ConstantNoHole(PropertyArray::HashField::kShift));
4361  } else {
4362  hash = effect = graph()->NewNode(
4363  simplified()->LoadField(AccessBuilder::ForPropertyArrayLengthAndHash()),
4364  properties, effect, control);
4365  hash = graph()->NewNode(
4366  simplified()->NumberBitwiseAnd(), hash,
4367  jsgraph()->ConstantNoHole(PropertyArray::HashField::kMask));
4368  }
4369  Node* new_length_and_hash =
4370  graph()->NewNode(simplified()->NumberBitwiseOr(),
4371  jsgraph()->ConstantNoHole(new_length), hash);
4372  // TDOO(jarin): Fix the typer to infer tighter bound for NumberBitwiseOr.
4373  new_length_and_hash = effect =
4374  graph()->NewNode(common()->TypeGuard(Type::SignedSmall()),
4375  new_length_and_hash, effect, control);
4376 
4377  // Allocate and initialize the new properties.
4378  AllocationBuilder a(jsgraph(), broker(), effect, control);
4379  a.Allocate(PropertyArray::SizeFor(new_length), AllocationType::kYoung,
4380  Type::OtherInternal());
4381  a.Store(AccessBuilder::ForMap(), jsgraph()->PropertyArrayMapConstant());
4382  a.Store(AccessBuilder::ForPropertyArrayLengthAndHash(), new_length_and_hash);
4383  for (int i = 0; i < new_length; ++i) {
4384  a.Store(AccessBuilder::ForFixedArraySlot(i), values[i]);
4385  }
4386  return a.Finish();
4387 }

4389 Node* JSNativeContextSpecialization::BuildCheckEqualsName(NameRef name,
4390  Node* value,
4391  Node* effect,
4392  Node* control) {
4393  DCHECK(name.IsUniqueName());
4394  Operator const* const op =
4395  name.IsSymbol() ? simplified()->CheckEqualsSymbol()
4396  : simplified()->CheckEqualsInternalizedString();
4397  return graph()->NewNode(op, jsgraph()->ConstantNoHole(name, broker()), value,
4398  effect, control);
4399 }

4401 bool JSNativeContextSpecialization::CanTreatHoleAsUndefined(
4402  ZoneVector<MapRef> const& receiver_maps) {
4403  // Check if all {receiver_maps} have one of the initial Array.prototype
4404  // or Object.prototype objects as their prototype (in any of the current
4405  // native contexts, as the global Array protector works isolate-wide).
4406  for (MapRef receiver_map : receiver_maps) {
4407  ObjectRef receiver_prototype = receiver_map.prototype(broker());
4408  if (!receiver_prototype.IsJSObject() ||
4409  !broker()->IsArrayOrObjectPrototype(receiver_prototype.AsJSObject())) {
4410  return false;
4411  }
4412  }
4413 
4414  // Check if the array prototype chain is intact.
4415  return dependencies()->DependOnNoElementsProtector();
4416 }
4417 
4418 bool JSNativeContextSpecialization::InferMaps(Node* object, Effect effect,
4419  ZoneVector<MapRef>* maps) const {
4420  ZoneRefSet<Map> map_set;
4421  NodeProperties::InferMapsResult result =
4422  NodeProperties::InferMapsUnsafe(broker(), object, effect, &map_set);
4423  if (result == NodeProperties::kReliableMaps) {
4424  for (MapRef map : map_set) {
4425  maps->push_back(map);
4426  }
4427  return true;
4428  } else if (result == NodeProperties::kUnreliableMaps) {
4429  // For untrusted maps, we can still use the information
4430  // if the maps are stable.
4431  for (MapRef map : map_set) {
4432  if (!map.is_stable()) return false;
4433  }
4434  for (MapRef map : map_set) {
4435  maps->push_back(map);
4436  }
4437  return true;
4438  }
4439  return false;
4440 }

4442 OptionalMapRef JSNativeContextSpecialization::InferRootMap(Node* object) const {
4443  HeapObjectMatcher m(object);
4444  if (m.HasResolvedValue()) {
4445  MapRef map = m.Ref(broker()).map(broker());
4446  return map.FindRootMap(broker());
4447  } else if (m.IsJSCreate()) {
4448  OptionalMapRef initial_map =
4449  NodeProperties::GetJSCreateMap(broker(), object);
4450  if (initial_map.has_value()) {
4451  DCHECK(initial_map->equals(initial_map->FindRootMap(broker())));
4452  return *initial_map;
4453  }
4454  }
4455  return std::nullopt;
4456 }

4458 Node* JSNativeContextSpecialization::BuildLoadPrototypeFromObject(
4459  Node* object, Node* effect, Node* control) {
4460  Node* map = effect =
4461  graph()->NewNode(simplified()->LoadField(AccessBuilder::ForMap()), object,
4462  effect, control);
4463  return graph()->NewNode(
4464  simplified()->LoadField(AccessBuilder::ForMapPrototype()), map, effect,
4465  control);
4466 }

4468 std::pair<Node*, Node*>
4469 JSNativeContextSpecialization::ReleaseEffectAndControlFromAssembler(
4470  JSGraphAssembler* gasm) {
4471  auto catch_scope = gasm->catch_scope();
4472  DCHECK(catch_scope->is_outermost());
4473 
4474  if (catch_scope->has_handler() &&
4475  catch_scope->has_exceptional_control_flow()) {
4476  TNode<Object> handler_exception;
4477  Effect handler_effect{nullptr};
4478  Control handler_control{nullptr};
4479  gasm->catch_scope()->MergeExceptionalPaths(
4480  &handler_exception, &handler_effect, &handler_control);
4481 
4482  ReplaceWithValue(gasm->outermost_handler(), handler_exception,
4483  handler_effect, handler_control);
4484  }
4485 
4486  return {gasm->effect(), gasm->control()};
4487 }
